<node id="Matthew Tancik">
  <data key="d0">Matthew Tancik</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Matthew Tancik is a researcher and author known for influential work on neural radiance fields and related scene representation methods for view synthesis and real-time rendering. He is listed as an author of NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis, where he is also marked as an equal contributor. The descriptions consistently associate him with the foundational NeRF paper and identify him as one of its cited authors.

Matthew Tancik is also credited as an author of several important follow-on works in the same research area, including Mip-NeRF: A Multiscale Representation for Anti-Aliasing Neural Radiance Fields, Plenoxels: Radiance Fields without Neural Networks, and PlenOctrees for Real-time Rendering of Neural Radiance Fields. In addition, he is listed as an author of the Gsplat white paper. Taken together, these descriptions portray Matthew Tancik as a significant contributor to the development of neural radiance fields, anti-aliased multiscale representations, non-neural radiance field formulations, and efficient rendering techniques.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95e7570668ab2add22a107c42e84d859&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24800bbb3bf5dc8182a3f3b86a0d5dad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb5c9e689ffa78ae20907ec96c23e19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45d73dd21f95946d74e1b943beb1d384&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee99e1fe0369d50218c77432ff216939</data>
