<node id="TripoSR">
  <data key="d0">TripoSR</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">TripoSR refers primarily to a production-quality, open release of a feed-forward 3D reconstruction system for generating a 3D object from a single image. It is described as an official released model, an open-weights variant in the Large Reconstruction Model (LRM) line, and a rebuilt version of LRM trained with improved data and training procedures. Across the descriptions, TripoSR is characterized as a fast, state-of-the-art, open-source or open production-quality system designed to produce high-quality 3D models rapidly from single-image input. It is also positioned within the feed-forward reconstruction family as a method used for direct benchmarking, including head-to-head comparison against SDS-on-splats, and is described as a feed-forward single-image-to-3D approach that appeared after Magic123.

TripoSR can also refer to a 2024 scholarly article about fast 3D object reconstruction from a single image. In that sense, the name denotes not only the released model itself but also the associated research publication that presents the method and its technical framing. Together, these descriptions indicate that TripoSR is both a notable research contribution and a widely recognized open release in the feed-forward single-image 3D reconstruction line.&lt;SEP&gt;TripoSR is later work identified as following the same general fast Text-to-3D template as Instant3D.&lt;SEP&gt;TripoSR is a FeedForward single-image 3D reconstruction model that returns a mesh from a single image in under half a second while improving reconstruction quality on standard benchmarks.&lt;SEP&gt;TripoSR is a feed-forward NeRF-style generator cited as a prior method whose training-time compute scaled poorly with output resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21872029f2f74d4a8d748cb5926862f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5bb0a18f713e04fc8443e094f65e4d3f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d220499711c1162411863777d237e45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c7d76e53023a8dbf570b925a45a1d01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
