<node id="Large Reconstruction Model">
  <data key="d0">Large Reconstruction Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Large Reconstruction Model is the model family that TripoSR is described as a feed-forward variant of.&lt;SEP&gt;Large Reconstruction Model is a feed-forward single-image 3D reconstruction method that maps an input image to the parameters of a NeRF-style radiance field in a single forward pass using a 500-million-parameter Transformer.&lt;SEP&gt;Large Reconstruction Model is the second-stage reconstructor in Instant3D that predicts a radiance field from sparse multi-view input in one forward pass.</data>
