<node id="Instant3D">
  <data key="d0">Instant3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Instant3D is a feed-forward 3D generation method that appears in later work following systems such as Magic123, ProlificDreamer, and DreamGaussian. It is described as inheriting analytical insights from ProlificDreamer while pursuing alternative 3D representations, and as a later Gaussian-based generator motivated by DreamGaussian.

Across the descriptions, Instant3D is characterized by a pipeline that reduces ambiguity before 3D reconstruction by placing a multi-view diffusion stage in front of an LRM-style backbone. It first generates a sparse set of consistent object views, often described as four views, and then feeds those views into an LRM to regress a 3D radiance field in a single forward pass. In this sense, Instant3D is presented both as a single-image-to-3D method and as a text-to-3D pipeline, with the common principle being that multi-view generation is chained into the reconstruction model to make the input less ambiguous and enable fast feed-forward 3D synthesis.

Instant3D is also noted in comparative evaluation practice, where it widely uses TripoSR as a comparison baseline.&lt;SEP&gt;Instant3D is a downstream multi-view diffusion style referenced as a pairing pattern for TripoSR pipelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Instant3D is a feed-forward NeRF-style generator cited as a prior method whose training-time compute scaled poorly with output resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21872029f2f74d4a8d748cb5926862f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d220499711c1162411863777d237e45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
