<node id="SDS Distillation Paradigm">
  <data key="d0">SDS Distillation Paradigm</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The SDS Distillation Paradigm is described as the approach launched by DreamFusion in 2022 and is presented as being quietly deprecated in favor of cheaper splatting-native variants or feed-forward reconstruction models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DreamFusion">
  <data key="d0">DreamFusion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DreamFusion is a 2022 text-to-3D method introduced by Poole et al. that is widely recognized as the paper that established Score Distillation Sampling (SDS) for 3D generation. It generates 3D content from natural-language prompts by using a pretrained 2D text-to-image diffusion model as a critic and backpropagating that model’s score into a scene-specific 3D representation, typically a NeRF, through per-view renderings. A notable aspect of DreamFusion is that it does not require 3D training data and does not require modifying the underlying diffusion model.

DreamFusion is often described as the first work to propagate guidance from a 2D diffusion model into a per-scene 3D optimization process, making it a foundational earlier text-to-3D approach. Its generation pipeline relies on per-instance SDS optimization, and the SDS loss used in later work is commonly traced back to DreamFusion. The method is also referenced for prompting strategies such as viewpoint-specific text prompts.

At the same time, DreamFusion is frequently characterized by its practical limitations. It is slower than later follow-up systems, often requiring hours to produce a single asset, and its outputs are sometimes described as having cartoonish geometry. As a result, it is commonly used as a baseline or comparison point: Magic3D is presented as a faster, higher-spatial-resolution successor to DreamFusion, while LRM is described as orders of magnitude faster at inference than DreamFusion’s per-instance SDS pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is a per-prompt SDS system used as a speed comparison baseline for Instant3D.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is a prior text-to-3D work cited as the 2022 source of Score Distillation Sampling and as one side of the line that Zero-1-to-3 connected to single-image-to-3D work.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is a method that uses a NeRF backbone and serves as the baseline architecture that DreamGaussian modifies.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is an earlier optimisation-based implicit SDS method that is slower than DreamGaussian.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is an optimisation-based 3D generator cited as part of the prior landscape before LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d585a450d31daf1370ab99c3ececfb44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2211-10440/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Magic3D">
  <data key="d0">Magic3D</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Magic3D is a paper in the SDS line that added a coarse-to-fine schedule with a mesh-export second stage.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a 2022 paper and method for high-resolution text-to-3D content creation that uses a two-stage coarse-to-fine pipeline to produce high-quality textured 3D meshes.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a 2022 paper by Lin et al. that presents a coarse-to-fine, mesh-export approach with a low-resolution NeRF stage followed by high-resolution textured-mesh refinement.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a subsequent radiance-field method that uses the hash encoding for text-to-3D.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a later work in the text-to-3D literature presented as part of the line of research seeded by DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a work in the corpus described as extending Stable-DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic3D is a text-to-3D follow-on line referenced alongside DreamFusion in the context of Zero-1-to-3 connecting text-to-3D and single-image-to-3D research.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71173d9786b13b28dc182e4c921d912b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2211-10440/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2201-05989/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zero-1-to-3">
  <data key="d0">Zero-1-to-3</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Zero-1-to-3 is a paper that reconditioned a diffusion model on camera pose so that the prior had geometric structure rather than only appearance-level structure.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3 is a 2023 paper by Liu et al. that fine-tunes Stable Diffusion to condition on camera pose relative to a reference image, making the prior geometric rather than only appearance-based.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3 is a single-image method presented as part of the later literature influenced by DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3 is a pretrained model required for image-conditioned 3D generation and used for the diffusion backend.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3 is a paper and framework that generates new views of an object from a single RGB image and supports single-view 3D reconstruction by re-purposing geometric priors from a pretrained text-to-image diffusion model.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3 is an image-conditioned diffusion prior that DreamGaussian distills into its 3D Gaussian Splatting representation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cee14ff0001178656f392a3bf199e70c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d585a450d31daf1370ab99c3ececfb44</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876216</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Magic123">
  <data key="d0">Magic123</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Magic123 is a 2023 paper by Qian et al. that presents a coarse-to-fine image-to-3D pipeline for recovering a textured 3D mesh from a single unposed photograph. Magic123 explicitly combines the complementary priors introduced by Magic3D and Zero-1-to-3, and is also described in the corpus as an extension of Stable-DreamFusion. Its core contribution is to unify appearance richness and geometric consistency by pairing a 2D Stable Diffusion score distillation sampling (SDS) loss with a 3D Zero-1-to-3 SDS loss.

Within the broader literature, Magic123 is characterized as an optimization-based, per-instance or per-prompt implicit SDS method rather than a fast feed-forward model. Because of this design, it is frequently used as a speed comparison baseline: LRM is described as orders of magnitude faster at inference, Instant3D uses it as a per-prompt SDS baseline, and DreamGaussian is presented as faster than this earlier optimization-based approach. The corpus also notes that Magic123 functions as a downstream method that relies on the repository’s checkpoint and inference scripts. Overall, Magic123 is best understood as a single-image 3D generation method that bridges strong 2D appearance priors and 3D geometric priors, while also serving as a common baseline for later, more efficient 3D generation systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Magic123 is an optimisation-based 3D generator cited as part of the prior landscape before LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ProlificDreamer">
  <data key="d0">ProlificDreamer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">ProlificDreamer is a paper in the SDS line that reframed SDS as a variational problem through Variational Score Distillation and removed mode collapse.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is a full text-to-3D generation pipeline that uses Variational Score Distillation to produce high-fidelity and diverse 3D outputs, including 512×512 NeRF renders and editable assets after mesh fine-tuning.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is a 2023 paper by Wang et al. that reframes SDS as a particle-based variational approximation called Variational Score Distillation and largely removes the mode-collapse issues of vanilla SDS.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is a later work in the text-to-3D literature presented as following DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is a work in the corpus described as extending Stable-DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is a per-prompt SDS system used as a speed comparison baseline for Instant3D.&lt;SEP&gt;ProlificDreamer is an optimisation-based 3D generator cited as part of the prior landscape before LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Variational Score Distillation">
  <data key="d0">Variational Score Distillation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Variational Score Distillation is the variational reformulation of SDS introduced by ProlificDreamer.&lt;SEP&gt;Variational Score Distillation is a particle-based variational approximation of SDS introduced by ProlificDreamer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875139</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DreamGaussian">
  <data key="d0">DreamGaussian</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DreamGaussian is a 2023 research paper, titled DreamGaussian: Generative Gaussian Splatting for Efficient 3D Content Creation, associated with Tang et al. It presents an efficient method for 3D content creation based on generative Gaussian splatting and is positioned within the diffusion-to-3D research line. The work is described as bridging that line of research into the 3D Gaussian splatting representation, explicitly replacing the NeRF-style backbone used in earlier approaches with 3D Gaussians.

DreamGaussian is also characterized as a per-scene optimization-based pipeline in which Gaussians are optimized against an SDS critic. In this sense, it is both a Gaussian-based 3D generator and a later work that builds on analysis inherited from ProlificDreamer while adopting a different 3D representation. A central contribution attributed to DreamGaussian is its dramatic efficiency improvement: by substituting 3D Gaussians for the previous backbone, it reduces per-asset generation cost from hours to minutes, with some descriptions specifying roughly two minutes per asset.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamGaussian is a generative 3D method for efficient 3D content creation that uses 3D Gaussian Splatting, distills a Zero-1-to-3 image-conditioned diffusion prior through SDS, and extracts a textured mesh.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamGaussian is a paper that presents a generative 3D content creation approach using Gaussian Splatting to achieve major speed improvements without sacrificing fidelity.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamGaussian is a downstream method in the corpus that depends on the checkpoint and inference scripts from the repository.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamGaussian is an optimisation-based 3D generator cited as part of the prior landscape before LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-627ca88fd03d8564307be09b989be23c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d220499711c1162411863777d237e45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d585a450d31daf1370ab99c3ececfb44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/inference-cost-vs-fidelity.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Gaussians">
  <data key="d0">3D Gaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">3D Gaussians is a representation used as the backbone in DreamGaussian and as the basis for cheaper per-asset generation.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are explicit primitives used as the map or scene representation in Gaussian splatting methods.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are used in DreamGaussian as a replacement for the NeRF backbone in SDS, enabling much faster asset generation.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are the scene representation introduced in the paper, preserving desirable properties of continuous volumetric radiance fields while avoiding unnecessary computation in empty space.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are the explicit scene representation used by GS-SLAM and MonoGS instead of implicit volumes.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are the explicit primitives grown, densified, pruned, and rendered by DreamGaussian during generation.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussians are the geometric primitives whose core differentiable rasterization is re-implemented by Gsplat.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5c7f1e459e9c1753c0a4eb10eae7e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-30/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876467</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LucidDreamer">
  <data key="d0">LucidDreamer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LucidDreamer is a text-to-Gaussian-scene generalization of the DreamGaussian-style paradigm.&lt;SEP&gt;LucidDreamer is a contemporary approach in open-domain scene generation that differs from GALA3D in how scene structure is obtained.&lt;SEP&gt;LucidDreamer is a pipeline that generates large 3D scenes using off-the-shelf 2D diffusion priors and no scene-scale 3D training data by lifting generated images into a point cloud and converting the result into a Gaussian Splatting scene.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fd2757a4334bd3990412235a6cbd419</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-13384/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876027</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GALA3D">
  <data key="d0">GALA3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">GALA3D is a paper that extends the Gaussian-based paradigm to layout-guided compositional scenes.&lt;SEP&gt;GALA3D is a compositional TextTo3D pipeline designed for complex multi-object scene generation, joint scene refinement, and per-object controllable editing.&lt;SEP&gt;GALA3D is a scene-level method mentioned as related work alongside LucidDreamer in emerging Gaussian-based open-domain 3D content creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fd2757a4334bd3990412235a6cbd419</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-13384/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876027</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AGG">
  <data key="d0">AGG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">AGG is the amortized single-image variant within the Gaussian-based line described in the synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;AGG is a feed-forward Gaussian predictor included in the family of methods for which MVSplat has become a reference point.&lt;SEP&gt;AGG is a paper and model described as an amortized generative approach that produces a 3D Gaussian Splatting representation from a single input image in a single forward pass.&lt;SEP&gt;AGG is a feed-forward Gaussian generator enabled downstream by the Diffusion-based 3D Generation section opened by DreamGaussian.&lt;SEP&gt;AGG is a later feed-forward Gaussian-based generator motivated by DreamGaussian.&lt;SEP&gt;AGG is a method identified as part of the Gaussian-prediction line of work alongside LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d585a450d31daf1370ab99c3ececfb44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Feed-Forward Large Reconstruction Models">
  <data key="d0">Feed-Forward Large Reconstruction Models</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Feed-Forward Large Reconstruction Models are presented as a competing replacement for per-scene SDS optimization by reconstructing 3D outputs without a per-scene optimization loop.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W18/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Objaverse">
  <data key="d0">Objaverse</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Objaverse is the dataset on which LRM is trained.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is the dataset on which LRM is trained.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is the source of the renderings and the original licenses for individual rendered objects.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is a publicly released dataset or resource acknowledged as part of the work's related resources.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is the training data referenced for finetuning the default 105000.ckpt checkpoint.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is a dataset providing synthetic renders that are used in the training corpus for LRM.&lt;SEP&gt;Objaverse is the training source referenced for the checkpoint provided by the repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b3dc42246e28acdc27923c03fab11c12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d220499711c1162411863777d237e45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cab660adb0c0033bdf9b7cb3ec02bfd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc</data>
