<node id="Image+Text-To-3D">
  <data key="d0">Image+Text-To-3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Image+Text-To-3D is a workflow that generates 3D content from both an image input and a text prompt.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Gaussian Stage">
  <data key="d0">Training Gaussian Stage</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Gaussian Stage is a processing stage executed with `python main.py` for image, text, and image-plus-text 3D generation workflows.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Mesh Stage">
  <data key="d0">Training Mesh Stage</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Mesh Stage is a processing stage executed with `python main2.py`, can auto-load a coarse mesh, refine iterations, and export a fine mesh to logs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Visualization">
  <data key="d0">Visualization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Visualization is a workflow for viewing meshes, saving 360 degree videos, and saving multi-view images by using `kire`.&lt;SEP&gt;Visualization is an optional DROID-SLAM capability that can be installed separately and is stated not to work in the multi-GPU setting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833bec7f18854880457df56d1a16dbb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876659</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CLIP-Similarity Evaluation">
  <data key="d0">CLIP-Similarity Evaluation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">CLIP-Similarity Evaluation is a workflow that evaluates similarity between an input image and a generated mesh by using `python -m kiui.cli.clip_sim`.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OpenGL">
  <data key="d0">OpenGL</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">OpenGL is the graphics system whose world and camera coordinate convention is used by the project and whose errors are discussed in troubleshooting guidance.&lt;SEP&gt;OpenGL is a graphics dependency whose faulty installation can cause `eglInitialize()` failure.&lt;SEP&gt;OpenGL is the system whose pose coordinate convention is used by run_nerf.py and the other code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45d73dd21f95946d74e1b943beb1d384</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/bmild-nerf/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876879</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Force_Cuda_Rast">
  <data key="d0">Force_Cuda_Rast</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Force_Cuda_Rast is an option used to work around OpenGL initialization problems in both training and mesh rendering commands.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nvidia Driver">
  <data key="d0">Nvidia Driver</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Nvidia Driver is identified as a usual source of correct OpenGL installation for resolving EGL initialization issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Nvidia Driver is a system dependency that may need to be re-installed when OpenGL-related initialization fails.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian-Splatting">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian-Splatting</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian-Splatting is an acknowledged research work and open-source project that the work builds on.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian-Splatting is an explicit rendering representation combined with Score Distillation Sampling in later higher-fidelity methods descended from Magic3D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2211-10440/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874624</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Threestudio">
  <data key="d0">Threestudio</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Threestudio is an acknowledged open-source project that the work builds on.&lt;SEP&gt;Threestudio is a project that showcases image-to-3D results and implements single-view 3D reconstruction with zero123.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875428</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DearPyGui">
  <data key="d0">DearPyGui</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">DearPyGui is an acknowledged open-source project that the work builds on.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tang2023DreamGaussian">
  <data key="d0">Tang2023DreamGaussian</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Tang2023DreamGaussian is the cited article titled `DreamGaussian: Generative Gaussian Splatting for Efficient 3D Content Creation`, published as an arXiv preprint in 2023.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="World Coordinate System">
  <data key="d0">World Coordinate System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">World Coordinate System is defined as using the same convention as OpenGL, with axes labeled +x, +y, and +z.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Camera Coordinate System">
  <data key="d0">Camera Coordinate System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Camera Coordinate System is defined as using the same convention as OpenGL, with directions labeled up, target, right, and forward.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Configs/Image.Yaml">
  <data key="d0">Configs/Image.Yaml</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Configs/Image.Yaml is a configuration file referenced for additional options in the image-based workflow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Configs/Text.Yaml">
  <data key="d0">Configs/Text.Yaml</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Configs/Text.Yaml is a configuration file referenced for additional options in the text-based workflow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Configs/Text_Mv.Yaml">
  <data key="d0">Configs/Text_Mv.Yaml</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Configs/Text_Mv.Yaml is a configuration file referenced for additional options in the MVDream text-based workflow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e519888baab63d10a462c579c81bb3e3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/dreamgaussian-dreamgaussian/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874605</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Does Dynamic Reconstruction Work at Minute-Scale Capture in the Wild?">
  <data key="d0">Does Dynamic Reconstruction Work at Minute-Scale Capture in the Wild?</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Does Dynamic Reconstruction Work at Minute-Scale Capture in the Wild? is an open question about whether current dynamic reconstruction methods can handle several-minute hand-held monocular captures of complex real-world scenes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic Reconstruction is the research line discussed in the corpus, focused on reconstructing scenes with motion over time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="In the Wild Regime">
  <data key="d0">In the Wild Regime</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">In the Wild Regime is the concrete target setting of a hand-held monocular phone video lasting several minutes with multiple moving subjects and non-trivial illumination change in scenes such as a busy street or marketplace.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Benchmark Dataset of Multi-Minute Monocular Dynamic Captures">
  <data key="d0">Benchmark Dataset of Multi-Minute Monocular Dynamic Captures</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Benchmark Dataset of Multi-Minute Monocular Dynamic Captures is the proposed dataset containing calibrated ground truth for several-minute monocular dynamic captures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Failure Modes">
  <data key="d0">Failure Modes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Failure Modes are the expected breakdown mechanisms of current methods on long, unconstrained dynamic captures, including limited deformation capacity, canonical-frame breakdown, and temporal trajectory growth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deformation MLP">
  <data key="d0">Deformation MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Deformation MLP is the learned deformation component whose capacity is fixed at training time and is identified as a likely source of failure on longer captures.&lt;SEP&gt;Deformation MLP is the neural network component in Nerfies that models deformation and is optimized jointly with the radiance MLP.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Canonical-Frame Assumption">
  <data key="d0">Canonical-Frame Assumption</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Canonical-Frame Assumption is the assumption that a single canonical state can cover the capture, and it is identified as breaking on long complex dynamic videos.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Per-Gaussian Temporal Trajectories">
  <data key="d0">Per-Gaussian Temporal Trajectories</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Per-Gaussian Temporal Trajectories are the time-varying trajectories used in 4DGS-class methods, and their growth is described as linear in primitive count.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-Time 4D Rendering">
  <data key="d0">Real-Time 4D Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-Time 4D Rendering is the capability of rendering dynamic novel views in real time, which the field is publishing on short captures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c8af96ec09c34cba6b3e20e9e006eedc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/dynamic-reconstruction-scale.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874606</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
