<node id="LPIPS">
  <data key="d0">LPIPS</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">LPIPS is a perceptual image-quality evaluation metric used in computer vision to measure how similar a generated, rendered, or reconstructed image is to a reference image in a way that better matches human visual perception than strictly pixel-based metrics. It is used to assess perceptual similarity, visual fidelity, reconstruction quality, rendering quality, and overall perceptual realism, particularly in cases where human-perceived quality is more important than exact pixel agreement.

Across the provided descriptions, LPIPS is consistently presented as a standard evaluation metric in paper metadata, experimental reports, and standalone script results. It is explicitly listed as a metric for evaluating papers and their results, including reconstruction-focused and SLAM-related work such as SuGaR and GS-SLAM: Dense Visual SLAM with 3D Gaussian Splatting. Repeated references to LPIPS in evaluation sections indicate that it functions as an established quantitative benchmark for comparing methods.

The descriptions also show that LPIPS is broadly adopted across modern 3D vision, neural rendering, SLAM, reconstruction, and generative modeling research. It is associated with works such as DreamGaussian, Gaussian Splatting SLAM, AGG, Zero-1-to-3, LucidDreamer, MERF, Co-SLAM, latentSplat, Point-SLAM, HyperNeRF, NeRF-W, Plenoxels, DreamFusion, Direct Sparse Odometry, Magic123, NICE-SLAM, MonoSDF, Magic3D, NeuS, ProlificDreamer, UNISURF, GALA3D, and Neural Radiance Fields more broadly. Taken together, these descriptions characterize LPIPS as a widely recognized and commonly reported benchmark for evaluating output quality in state-of-the-art visual generation and reconstruction systems.&lt;SEP&gt;LPIPS is a metric listed for evaluating Feature 3DGS.&lt;SEP&gt;LPIPS is a metric listed for evaluating the paper's method.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-137c1bc42e741b7a6e96b6ddc476e477&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65491bb40aaff28e47124705eb1fff58&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24800bbb3bf5dc8182a3f3b86a0d5dad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71173d9786b13b28dc182e4c921d912b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a36dbf1bfe982e8516ef5fb0a1dd0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a914c77868426e1f8d5848af2165c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fd2757a4334bd3990412235a6cbd419&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c8a391c236226d67322607a99b2e56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add2de44399af98e378bc92e1b3f3d85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61a153082bbdd12d0fece3ecc8442ad9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6fcd8824908a999c0b58a88cfc0f735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c76c39f593d0f7cf762ef607bb98a3db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
