h/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-13384/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2302-12249/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2404-06109/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2105-06468/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-06741/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2002-10099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-12775/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Diffusion is a method listed for Magic3D and is used through diffusion-model-based supervision in the pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is listed as one of the methods associated with ProlificDreamer.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is the family of priors used by Magic123 to guide object generation through both 2D and 3D mechanisms.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is the text-to-image modeling approach fine-tuned in Instant3D to emit four structured and view-consistent images.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is a method listed for Zero-1-to-3 and is the generative modeling approach underlying the framework.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is the prior used in DreamGaussian to provide guidance for 3D generation and texture refinement.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion is a method used in the LGM pipeline to generate a small set of consistent multi-view images of a target object.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2211-10440/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hash Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Hash Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Hash Encoding is a method listed for Magic3D and corresponds to the hash-grid acceleration used in the coarse radiance-field stage.&lt;SEP&gt;Hash encoding is an underlying technique from which new models can be built.&lt;SEP&gt;Hash Encoding is an underlying representation that can be edited and trained on a new task by using the Tiny-CUDA-NN PyTorch Extension.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c0c63708e1adea212beb7d6e83516771&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2211-10440/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scaffold-GS">
  <data key="d0">Scaffold-GS</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Scaffold-GS is a structured 3D Gaussian rendering method that uses a two-tier representation with sparse anchor points and view-conditioned neural Gaussians to reduce redundant primitives and improve robustness under viewpoint change, texture-less regions, and view-dependent lighting.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is a 2023 paper that replaces free Gaussians with anchor points that emit view-conditioned offsets, pruning redundant primitives in low-frequency regions.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is a referenced work that argues free Gaussian soup wastes capacity in low-frequency regions and is complemented by Revising Densification.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is follow-on work that replaces a free Gaussian soup with anchor-based structure.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is a structural variant in the Gaussian Splatting literature that changes the primitive itself rather than the densification schedule.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is a downstream method that plugs into the CUDA kernels of Gsplat.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a8a7270af8c939590a0f9c7697a5b90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add2de44399af98e378bc92e1b3f3d85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-25/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2404-06109/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876468</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scaffold-GS: Structured 3D Gaussians for View-Adaptive Rendering">
  <data key="d0">Scaffold-GS: Structured 3D Gaussians for View-Adaptive Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Scaffold-GS: Structured 3D Gaussians for View-Adaptive Rendering is a paper describing the Scaffold-GS method for view-adaptive rendering with structured 3D Gaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anchor Points">
  <data key="d0">Anchor Points</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Anchor Points are sparse points placed near scene geometry that form the scaffold in Scaffold-GS and each own a small bundle of neural Gaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Neural Gaussians">
  <data key="d0">Neural Gaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Neural Gaussians are per-anchor primitives in Scaffold-GS whose position offset, opacity, colour, and scale are predicted on the fly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Shared MLP">
  <data key="d0">Shared MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Shared MLP is the network in Scaffold-GS that predicts neural Gaussian attributes from viewing direction and camera-to-anchor distance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Viewing Direction">
  <data key="d0">Viewing Direction</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Viewing Direction is an input to the shared MLP in Scaffold-GS and conditions how neural Gaussian attributes are predicted.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Camera-To-Anchor Distance">
  <data key="d0">Camera-To-Anchor Distance</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Camera-To-Anchor Distance is an input to the shared MLP in Scaffold-GS and helps condition neural Gaussian attribute prediction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scene Geometry">
  <data key="d0">Scene Geometry</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Scene Geometry is the underlying structural information in a scene that vanilla 3D Gaussian Splatting tends to ignore and that Scaffold-GS uses to place anchor points.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Procedure">
  <data key="d0">Training Procedure</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Procedure is the Scaffold-GS process that grows and prunes anchor points based on contribution to rendering quality, expanding into under-covered regions and removing anchors whose neural Gaussians never fire.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rendering Quality">
  <data key="d0">Rendering Quality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rendering Quality is the criterion used to score anchor contributions during Scaffold-GS training and is maintained while reducing primitive count.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Primitive Count">
  <data key="d0">Primitive Count</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Primitive Count is the number of rendering primitives, which Scaffold-GS substantially reduces at equal rendering quality.&lt;SEP&gt;Primitive Count is the quantity of primitives that remains the same while fidelity improves in Revising Densification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="View-Adaptive Rendering">
  <data key="d0">View-Adaptive Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">View-Adaptive Rendering is the capability of producing different splat patterns from different viewing angles through view-conditioned prediction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Level-Of-Detail Scenarios">
  <data key="d0">Level-Of-Detail Scenarios</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Level-Of-Detail Scenarios are evaluation situations in which Scaffold-GS shows improved robustness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="View-Extrapolation Scenarios">
  <data key="d0">View-Extrapolation Scenarios</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">View-Extrapolation Scenarios are evaluation situations involving large viewpoint changes in which Scaffold-GS shows improved robustness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Structured Gaussian Representations">
  <data key="d0">Structured Gaussian Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Structured Gaussian Representations are a line of work that uses structured forms of Gaussian scene representation and for which Scaffold-GS became a common starting point.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
