</node>
<node id="Texture-Less Regions">
  <data key="d0">Texture-Less Regions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Texture-Less Regions are scene areas identified as difficult for vanilla 3D Gaussian Splatting because the representation lacks shared structure across views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="View-Dependent Lighting Effects">
  <data key="d0">View-Dependent Lighting Effects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">View-Dependent Lighting Effects are appearance changes across viewing angles that vanilla 3D Gaussian Splatting handles poorly without shared multi-view structure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anchor Density">
  <data key="d0">Anchor Density</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Anchor Density is the amount of anchors used in a structured Gaussian representation and is described as being varied by later extensions according to scene complexity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scene Complexity">
  <data key="d0">Scene Complexity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Scene Complexity is a scene property that later extensions use to vary anchor density in structured Gaussian representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Editing">
  <data key="d0">Editing</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Editing is an application area for later extensions that adapt the per-anchor MLP in structured Gaussian representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compression">
  <data key="d0">Compression</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compression is an application area for later extensions that adapt the per-anchor MLP in structured Gaussian representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4b8d422b0944627b01e7c77ba8f039d8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-00109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874645</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="hustvl/4DGaussians">
  <data key="d0">hustvl/4DGaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">hustvl/4DGaussians is the official implementation repository for 4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering and serves as an open reference for comparison with other dynamic 3D Gaussian Splatting papers.&lt;SEP&gt;hustvl/4DGaussians is the open-source repository listed in the paper metadata for the released code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb7662ca60286f5c929b6bb92d667dfd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2310-08528/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876658</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering">
  <data key="d0">4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering is the paper implemented by hustvl/4DGaussians and presents a method for real-time dynamic scene rendering.&lt;SEP&gt;4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering is the method presented by the repository and is described as converging quickly while achieving real-time rendering speed.&lt;SEP&gt;4D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering is a cited paper listed in the repository citation section.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-758b48d0e0102138cc11ccffdb5fff60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d7c1d8ea46e8d39c693dee7fccbb8f2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HexPlane-Style Spatio-Temporal Deformation Field">
  <data key="d0">HexPlane-Style Spatio-Temporal Deformation Field</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">HexPlane-Style Spatio-Temporal Deformation Field is a compact spatio-temporal deformation field attached to a canonical set of Gaussians in the method.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Canonical Set of Gaussians">
  <data key="d0">Canonical Set of Gaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Canonical Set of Gaussians is the Gaussian representation to which the deformation field is attached in the method.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic Scenes are scenes with motion that the method targets by extending 3D Gaussian Splatting.&lt;SEP&gt;Dynamic Scenes are time-varying scenes involving motion, topological changes, and appearing or disappearing content that the paper targets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-393d4b1d50fb3d20d718f84708cec66c</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-03307/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876987</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Video">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Video</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular Video is the input data source from which the method enables real-time rendering of moving content.&lt;SEP&gt;Monocular Video is the training input used to optimize Nerfies without explicit motion supervision.&lt;SEP&gt;Monocular Video is the single-view video input used by the method to reconstruct and synthesize a dynamic scene.&lt;SEP&gt;Monocular video is the training modality used to train DROID-SLAM end-to-end.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61a153082bbdd12d0fece3ecc8442ad9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2105-06468/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876760</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic Gaussians">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic Gaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic Gaussians is one of the corpus's dynamic 3D Gaussian Splatting papers compared against hustvl/4DGaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874662</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nerfies / HyperNeRF Lineage">
  <data key="d0">Nerfies / HyperNeRF Lineage</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Nerfies / HyperNeRF Lineage is a line of related work that is compared against hustvl/4DGaussians in the corpus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874662</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Apache-2.0">
  <data key="d0">Apache-2.0</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Apache-2.0 is the license under which hustvl/4DGaussians is mirrored.&lt;SEP&gt;Apache-2.0 is the license under which Stable-DreamFusion is mirrored.&lt;SEP&gt;Apache-2.0 is the license specified for the mirrored repository README.&lt;SEP&gt;Apache-2.0 is the license identified for the mirrored gsplat repository.&lt;SEP&gt;Apache-2.0 is the license under which Gsplat is mirrored in the repository description.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-758b48d0e0102138cc11ccffdb5fff60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876468</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="README">
  <data key="d0">README</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">README refers here to several distinct repository README files that share the same generic name but belong to different upstream projects. In each case, README denotes mirrored documentation text rather than source code, so the mirrored corpus includes descriptive project material while explicitly excluding the upstream implementation.

For VAST-AI-Research/TripoSR, README is the mirrored project documentation text, with the mirror explicitly excluding the source code. More generally, README is described as mirrored text content from an upstream project that is included in the repository mirror without the upstream code, and in one entry it is identified as the only included repository content mentioned in the description.

For the upstream Zero-1-to-3 repository, README is the mirrored project documentation copied from the upstream repository on 2026-05-15. This indicates a snapshot of the documentation text rather than a full repository mirror.

For NVlabs/instant-ngp, the README is mirrored from the upstream Instant-NGP project and is the only mirrored material included in the LLM-Wiki demo corpus for that repository entry. It is also described as the source content that is truncated in the LLM-Wiki Demo, with the full version remaining available upstream. Similarly, README is identified as the only mirrored content from the upstream NVlabs/instant-ngp repository in the corpus.

For hustvl/4DGaussians, README is likewise described as the only mirrored content mentioned for that repository. Across these descriptions, README consistently represents the sole mirrored documentation artifact for specific repository entries, serving as a text-only proxy for the upstream project while excluding code.&lt;SEP&gt;README is the only repository content mirrored in the LLM-Wiki demo corpus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eea3b682e8bd992578c8df7af80e379d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d77e66aa7cc152f532934b3e4405857&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ce2165eaaf1422a9b02235e41e20e20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77bbc3a5c1fbf4a8a4029857b6fa01b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/vast-ai-research-triposr/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876958</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="arxiv-2310-08528">
  <data key="d0">arxiv-2310-08528</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">arxiv-2310-08528 is the canonical paper identifier associated with hustvl/4DGaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eeca9db1414daed89ce6cb97dc521320</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874662</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bmild/Nerf">
  <data key="d0">Bmild/Nerf</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Bmild/Nerf is the original TensorFlow reference implementation of NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis and defines the canonical training loop and dataset loaders that became standard evaluation harnesses for later NeRF work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7f48440bc6fda3db02b120c1e8bca82</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/bmild-nerf/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874673</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis">
  <data key="d0">NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis is the paper associated with the repository and provides the context for the original reference implementation.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis is a paper published on 2020-03-19 that introduces Neural Radiance Fields for view synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis is the paper associated with the project and repository.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis is the cited 2020 paper describing NeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7f48440bc6fda3db02b120c1e8bca82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45d73dd21f95946d74e1b943beb1d384&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee99e1fe0369d50218c77432ff216939</data>
