<node id="Mip-NeRF">
  <data key="d0">Mip-NeRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Mip-NeRF is a later NeRF paper in the corpus that compares against the bmild/nerf baseline.&lt;SEP&gt;Mip-NeRF is a neural radiance field method that replaces infinitesimal rays with cones, uses conical frustums and integrated positional encoding, supports features at multiple scales with a single MLP, and reduces aliasing across varying image resolutions.&lt;SEP&gt;Mip-NeRF is prior work in the coordinate-MLP line and a baseline over which Instant-NGP achieves several orders of magnitude speedup on comparable hardware.&lt;SEP&gt;Mip-NeRF is an earlier neural radiance field method that is extended by Mip-NeRF 360 from object-centric capture to unbounded 360-degree scenes.&lt;SEP&gt;Mip-NeRF is a follow-up in the Neural Radiance Fields family associated with aliasing.&lt;SEP&gt;Mip-NeRF is an aliasing-aware revision of NeRF in which rays become cones and point samples become integrated positional encodings over conical frustums, making it useful on multiscale captures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e7f48440bc6fda3db02b120c1e8bca82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24800bbb3bf5dc8182a3f3b86a0d5dad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71173d9786b13b28dc182e4c921d912b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec770f62777c513047108cb79ba7aa75</data>
