  <data key="d5">1778876604</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF-W">
  <data key="d0">NeRF-W</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF-W is a later NeRF paper in the corpus that compares against the bmild/nerf baseline.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF-W is the extension introduced in the paper that models photometric variation and transient occluders for unconstrained landmark photo collections.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF-W is a follow-up in the Neural Radiance Fields family associated with in-the-wild settings.</data>
