</node>
<node id="Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Radiance fields are scene representations for which K-Planes provides a factorized explicit formulation spanning space, time, and appearance.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance fields are described as excellent at view synthesis but poor at directly producing a mesh.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance Fields are a class of neural graphics primitives and the broader field whose practical baseline was reset by Instant-NGP.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance fields are scene representations targeted by both 2D Gaussian Splatting and 3D Gaussian Splatting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e121a6c015eb471a5abd27b987476ced&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71173d9786b13b28dc182e4c921d912b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-20/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2201-05989/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876588</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TensoRF">
  <data key="d0">TensoRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">TensoRF is a prior method whose planar factorization is generalized by K-Planes.&lt;SEP&gt;TensoRF is a later method described as a direct descendant of Plenoxels.&lt;SEP&gt;TensoRF is a factorized representation whose decomposition pattern is mirrored by MERF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c8a391c236226d67322607a99b2e56</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2302-12249/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876128</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Static 3D Scene">
  <data key="d0">Static 3D Scene</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A static 3D scene is a scene type represented in K-Planes by three feature planes: xy, xz, and yz.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic 4D Scene">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic 4D Scene</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A dynamic 4D scene is a scene type represented in K-Planes by six feature planes: xy, xz, yz, xt, yt, and zt.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Small MLP">
  <data key="d0">Small MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A small MLP is a decoder option in K-Planes and prior factorized methods for mapping combined features into density and color.&lt;SEP&gt;Small MLP is the compact neural network that receives concatenated multilevel hash features as input to fit neural graphics primitives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71173d9786b13b28dc182e4c921d912b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2201-05989/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Linear Decoder">
  <data key="d0">Linear Decoder</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A linear decoder is a K-Planes decoder variant that, together with a learned global color basis, achieves comparable quality while keeping the pipeline white-box.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Learned Global Color Basis">
  <data key="d0">Learned Global Color Basis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A learned global color basis is used with the linear decoder in K-Planes to produce comparable rendering quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TV Penalty">
  <data key="d0">TV Penalty</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A TV penalty is used in K-Planes as a temporal smoothness prior applied to time-axis planes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-Resolution Stack of Spatial Planes">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Resolution Stack of Spatial Planes</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A multi-resolution stack of spatial planes is used in K-Planes to model multi-scale spatial detail.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Static-Dynamic Decomposition">
  <data key="d0">Static-Dynamic Decomposition</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Static-dynamic decomposition in K-Planes is induced by initializing time-involving planes to the identity so that those planes represent only genuinely time-varying content.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dense 4D Grid">
  <data key="d0">Dense 4D Grid</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A dense 4D grid is a baseline representation relative to which K-Planes achieves roughly 1000x memory compression.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874707</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PyTorch">
  <data key="d0">PyTorch</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">PyTorch is a software framework and core dependency across the described projects and tools. It is explicitly required for environments involving gsplat and DROID-SLAM, and it must be installed in a platform-appropriate way before those components are set up. The descriptions consistently emphasize that PyTorch’s CUDA version should align with the CUDA environment, particularly at the major-version level, so that the framework matches the installed CUDA runtime and local platform configuration.

PyTorch also serves as the implementation framework for multiple machine learning and graphics systems. It is the framework used to implement Stable-Dreamfusion, and it enables K-Planes to train efficiently without requiring custom CUDA code. In workflows involving Tiny-CUDA-NN, PyTorch is the framework through which that extension is used for editing and training. In addition, PyTorch is associated with rendering-related computations in which its computed spherical harmonics (SHs) and 3D covariance outputs can optionally be used during rendering. Overall, PyTorch is presented both as an essential installation dependency and as the operational framework underlying training, editing, and rendering pipelines in these systems.&lt;SEP&gt;PyTorch is the software framework used for the official implementation of Princeton-VL/DROID-SLAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-135c075dc7391afb1b0d603462e342e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ace087a61df1fdd6d045f0f39a3166c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cee14ff0001178656f392a3bf199e70c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833bec7f18854880457df56d1a16dbb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a57ecf4979daf463711507fe01462548</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2301-10241/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/vast-ai-research-triposr/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876675</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="sarafridov/K-Planes">
  <data key="d0">sarafridov/K-Planes</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
