</node>
<node id="Score Distillation Sampling (SDS)">
  <data key="d0">Score Distillation Sampling (SDS)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Score Distillation Sampling is described as the workhorse behind DreamFusion and related methods, but it suffers from over-saturation, over-smoothing, and collapse to low-diversity modes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Variational Score Distillation (VSD)">
  <data key="d0">Variational Score Distillation (VSD)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Variational Score Distillation is a particle-based variational framework that reformulates text-to-3D generation as posterior inference over a distribution of 3D scenes and updates an ensemble of 3D parameterisations using a learned variational score network and a pretrained prior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diffusion Prior">
  <data key="d0">Diffusion Prior</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Diffusion prior is a frozen pretrained text-to-image prior used in score distillation and related optimisation.&lt;SEP&gt;Diffusion Prior is the role assigned to the resulting model before it is used for SDS lifting to 3D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876990</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Variational Score Network">
  <data key="d0">Variational Score Network</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The variational score network is a learned component in Variational Score Distillation that updates the ensemble of 3D parameterisations alongside the pretrained prior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG)">
  <data key="d0">Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Classifier-Free Guidance is a guidance mechanism whose weights are used to evaluate the robustness of Variational Score Distillation, with standard CFG 7.5 producing diverse and detailed samples.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Slow-to-Fast Distillation Time Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Slow-to-Fast Distillation Time Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The slow-to-fast distillation time schedule is a companion design choice that improves performance and can be reused by other text-to-3D methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Density Initialisation">
  <data key="d0">Density Initialisation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Density initialisation is a companion design choice that provides additional gains in the ProlificDreamer framework and can be reused by other text-to-3D methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF Renders">
  <data key="d0">NeRF Renders</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF renders are 512×512 rendered outputs generated by the ProlificDreamer pipeline and are described as having fine structure and difficult visual effects such as smoke and translucency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mesh Fine-Tuning Stage">
  <data key="d0">Mesh Fine-Tuning Stage</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The mesh fine-tuning stage is a follow-on stage in ProlificDreamer that converts outputs into editable assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Text-to-3D Methods">
  <data key="d0">Text-to-3D Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Text-to-3D methods are generation approaches that can reuse design choices introduced alongside Variational Score Distillation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ArXiv 2305.16213">
  <data key="d0">ArXiv 2305.16213</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ArXiv 2305.16213 is the identifier assigned to the paper ProlificDreamer: High-Fidelity and Diverse Text-to-3D Generation with Variational Score Distillation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ScoreDistillation">
  <data key="d0">ScoreDistillation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">ScoreDistillation is listed as one of the methods associated with ProlificDreamer.&lt;SEP&gt;ScoreDistillation is an optimisation-based method used by contemporaneous ImageTo3D systems and is described as slow compared with LRM.&lt;SEP&gt;ScoreDistillation is a class of TextTo3D methods characterized in the paper as relying on slow per-prompt optimization.&lt;SEP&gt;ScoreDistillation is the optimization-based procedure around which earlier Gaussian-based 3D generators were built.&lt;SEP&gt;ScoreDistillation is the 3D generation framework whose implicit RadianceField backbone DreamGaussian replaces with an explicit GaussianSplatting representation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876451</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TextTo3D">
  <data key="d0">TextTo3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">TextTo3D is listed as one of the methods associated with ProlificDreamer.&lt;SEP&gt;TextTo3D is a generation approach that maps text descriptions to 3D content and is the task setting addressed by GALA3D.&lt;SEP&gt;TextTo3D is a method category focused on generating 3D content from text prompts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875863</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Variational">
  <data key="d0">Variational</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Variational is listed as one of the methods associated with ProlificDreamer.&lt;SEP&gt;Variational is a method designation listed for the latentSplat paper and reflects the paper's probabilistic treatment of 3D Gaussian representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a36dbf1bfe982e8516ef5fb0a1dd0e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-16292/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875535</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-Object Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Object Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-Object Scenes are 3D scenes containing several distinct entities whose separation, scale, and interactions must be maintained.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DreamFusion-Era Generators">
  <data key="d0">DreamFusion-Era Generators</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DreamFusion-Era Generators are described as typical single-object 3D generators that contrast with GALA3D's multi-object scene focus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SDS-Based Pipelines">
  <data key="d0">SDS-Based Pipelines</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">SDS-Based Pipelines are generation pipelines that tend to collapse when asked to produce scenes with several distinct entities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Large Language Model">
  <data key="d0">Large Language Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A Large Language Model is used at the start of the pipeline to translate a free-form scene description into an explicit layout.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLM-Generated Layout">
  <data key="d0">LLM-Generated Layout</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The LLM-Generated Layout is an explicit layout containing named objects, approximate bounding boxes, and qualitative relationships, and it serves as a prior for later optimisation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bounding Boxes">
  <data key="d0">Bounding Boxes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Bounding Boxes are approximate object-level spatial descriptions extracted into the layout and used to derive per-object geometric priors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874824</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GaussianSplatting Representation">
  <data key="d0">GaussianSplatting Representation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The GaussianSplatting Representation is a layout-guided representation in which Gaussians are organised into per-object groups and constrained by per-object geometric priors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874826</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Instance-Scene Compositional Optimisation Mechanism">
  <data key="d0">Instance-Scene Compositional Optimisation Mechanism</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Instance-Scene Compositional Optimisation Mechanism is a joint refinement stage that improves textures and shapes while adjusting layout scale, contact, and relative positions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874826</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Conditioned Diffusion Prior">
  <data key="d0">Conditioned Diffusion Prior</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Conditioned Diffusion Prior is the prior that drives the instance-scene compositional optimisation mechanism during joint refinement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874826</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Inpainting-Driven Point Cloud">
  <data key="d0">Inpainting-Driven Point Cloud</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Inpainting-Driven Point Cloud is the source of scene structure associated with LucidDreamer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e84795d808a30ea730dabef6dcde2d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-07207/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874826</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
