<node id="Jonathan T. Barron">
  <data key="d0">Jonathan T. Barron</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jonathan T. Barron is a researcher and author associated with a substantial body of work on neural radiance fields and related 3D generative and view-synthesis methods. He is credited as an author of NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis, a foundational work on representing scenes with neural radiance fields for novel-view rendering, as well as several major extensions and refinements of that line of research.

Jonathan T. Barron is also an author of NeRF in the Wild: Neural Radiance Fields for Unconstrained Photo Collections, which extends NeRF methods to more challenging real-world image collections, and of Mip-NeRF: A Multiscale Representation for Anti-Aliasing Neural Radiance Fields, which introduces a multiscale approach to reduce aliasing artifacts. In addition, he contributed to Mip-NeRF 360: Unbounded Anti-Aliased Neural Radiance Fields, which further develops anti-aliased NeRF techniques for unbounded scenes.

Beyond these contributions, Jonathan T. Barron is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields and HyperNeRF, both of which expand neural radiance field methods to model dynamic or more complex scene variations. He is also an author of DreamFusion, which connects these ideas to generative 3D synthesis, and of MERF, further demonstrating his involvement across influential advances in neural rendering, scene representation, and 3D generation.&lt;SEP&gt;Jonathan T. Barron is a listed author of the NeRF paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Jonathan T. Barron is an author of the cited NeRF paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24800bbb3bf5dc8182a3f3b86a0d5dad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c8a391c236226d67322607a99b2e56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45d73dd21f95946d74e1b943beb1d384&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee99e1fe0369d50218c77432ff216939</data>
