<node id="In-the-Wild Setting">
  <data key="d0">In-the-Wild Setting</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The In-the-Wild Setting is a capture setting based on tourist photo collections with variation in time of day, weather, exposure, and transient occluders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tourist Photo Collections">
  <data key="d0">Tourist Photo Collections</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Tourist Photo Collections are image collections of famous landmarks whose captures vary in appearance and often include people and vehicles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Per-Image Appearance Embedding">
  <data key="d0">Per-Image Appearance Embedding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Per-Image Appearance Embedding is a low-dimensional latent code concatenated to the radiance MLP input to model photometric variation while keeping geometry shared.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Radiance MLP">
  <data key="d0">Radiance MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Radiance MLP is the network input pathway to which the per-image appearance embedding is concatenated in NeRF-W.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance MLP is a larger neural network that supervises the proposal MLP and concentrates modeling capacity on visible content.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance MLP is the neural network component in Nerfies that models scene radiance and is optimized jointly with the deformation MLP.&lt;SEP&gt;Radiance MLP is the appearance component in the VolSDF representation, separated from the signed distance function shape representation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876784</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transient Head">
  <data key="d0">Transient Head</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Transient Head is a separate NeRF-W component conditioned on a per-image embedding that predicts transient density, color, and an uncertainty field.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Per-Image Embedding">
  <data key="d0">Per-Image Embedding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Per-Image Embedding is the conditioning signal used by the transient head in NeRF-W.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uncertainty Field">
  <data key="d0">Uncertainty Field</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Uncertainty Field is a predicted field in NeRF-W that downweights loss in pixels with inconsistent transient content.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Flickr">
  <data key="d0">Flickr</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Flickr is the source platform for the in-the-wild image collections used to reconstruct landmarks in the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-501dafee6515bd66912047d0b36d43f9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2008-02268/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
