<node id="Custom Image Set (360)">
  <data key="d0">Custom Image Set (360)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Custom Image Set (360) is a user-provided image collection captured around an object from multiple angles and elevations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02c51c541bd8838daa93cb2a36760941</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874886</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="COLMAP">
  <data key="d0">COLMAP</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">COLMAP is a structure-from-motion and multi-view reconstruction tool that is used in these workflows as a core preprocessing dependency for custom and real-image datasets. It must be installed before running the relevant preprocessing steps, and in some setups it is required alongside LLFF Code to compute camera poses from real data. More broadly, COLMAP serves as an example of a structure-from-motion pipeline used to estimate accurate camera poses before training.

In these pipelines, COLMAP also functions as a data source format: a dataset path in COLMAP format can be passed directly to the training script. Its outputs provide important geometric inputs to downstream training, including the sparse SfM point cloud used by the training pipeline and, in some cases, dense point clouds as well. For certain HyperNeRF scenes, pregenerated point clouds produced by COLMAP are provided.

COLMAP is therefore both a required software dependency and a source of reconstructed scene geometry for training workflows. At the same time, its reconstruction process is not guaranteed to succeed in every case, and it may fail to recover camera poses for some custom datasets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02c51c541bd8838daa93cb2a36760941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d8dc07a758da2f544255725b8c6e1a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee99e1fe0369d50218c77432ff216939&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77bbc3a5c1fbf4a8a4029857b6fa01b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/bmild-nerf/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876965</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="opt/scripts/proc_colmap.sh">
  <data key="d0">opt/scripts/proc_colmap.sh</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">opt/scripts/proc_colmap.sh is a script used to process an image directory with COLMAP for custom datasets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02c51c541bd8838daa93cb2a36760941</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874886</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Noradial">
  <data key="d0">Noradial</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Noradial is a recommended option for COLMAP processing because it avoids undistortion that can make results blurry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02c51c541bd8838daa93cb2a36760941</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874886</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OPENCV Camera Model">
  <data key="d0">OPENCV Camera Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">OPENCV Camera Model is a complete camera model mentioned as desirable future support for more recent projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02c51c541bd8838daa93cb2a36760941</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778874886</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
