<node id="Point-SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Point-SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Point-SLAM is a neural-SLAM paper in the continuation of the implicit-map SLAM line.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is a dense neural SLAM system that anchors the features of a neural scene representation in an incrementally grown point cloud, adapts anchor density to local information density, and shares the same point-based field across mapping and tracking.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is a neural-implicit SLAM follow-up named as part of the wave influenced by NICE-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is a SLAM method that replaces the grid representation with a neural point cloud to provide adaptive resolution where the scene needs it.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is identified as a direct predecessor to Gaussian-based incremental SLAM systems such as MonoGS and GS-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is a later neural-implicit SLAM system in the corpus that benchmarks against DROID-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;Point-SLAM is an earlier neural SLAM method that relies on implicit features anchored in points and reconstructs geometry through Neural Implicit Surface rendering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a914c77868426e1f8d5848af2165c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5c7f1e459e9c1753c0a4eb10eae7e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a57ecf4979daf463711507fe01462548&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-04278/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-12130/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-30/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-06741/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Co-SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Co-SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Co-SLAM is a neural-implicit SLAM method and real-time neural RGB-D SLAM system that belongs to the continuation of the implicit-map SLAM line, particularly the wave of follow-up work influenced by NICE-SLAM. It is described as a later neural-implicit SLAM system in its corpus, while also being an earlier neural SLAM approach relative to subsequent Gaussian-based incremental methods. In that lineage, Co-SLAM is identified as a direct predecessor to later systems such as MonoGS and GS-SLAM.

Technically, Co-SLAM uses a hybrid scene encoding that combines a multi-resolution hash grid with a coordinate-based one-blob encoding to support both tracking and mapping in real time. It is notable for re-introducing a sparse parametric encoding to improve speed, and it reuses the multiresolution hash grid design that became characteristic of this family of methods. The system relies on implicit features anchored in points or hash grids and reconstructs geometry through Neural Implicit Surface rendering.

Within the broader SLAM literature, Co-SLAM is positioned as a later neural-implicit SLAM system that benchmarks against DROID-SLAM. Overall, it stands as an important transitional method: it advances the implicit neural SLAM paradigm with efficient hybrid encoding and real-time RGB-D operation, while also helping bridge earlier neural implicit mapping approaches and later Gaussian-based incremental SLAM systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5c7f1e459e9c1753c0a4eb10eae7e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ce2165eaaf1422a9b02235e41e20e20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a57ecf4979daf463711507fe01462548&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-12130/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-30/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-06741/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
