<node id="Gaussian Splatting SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Splatting SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian Splatting SLAM is the SLAM variant that keeps keyframe management and joint optimisation while replacing the map with rasterised 3D Gaussians.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is a GaussianSplatting-based neural SLAM variant mentioned as part of a later wave of systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is a later SLAM approach cited as retaining the explicit-primitive philosophy of Point-SLAM while replacing point anchors with anisotropic Gaussian primitives.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is follow-on work that extends the representation to live camera tracking.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is a SLAM system mentioned as reusing or imitating gsplat's rasteriser interface.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is a paper dated 2023-12-11 that presents MonoGS as a monocular SLAM system based on 3D GaussianSplatting and discusses tracking, mapping, and novel view synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;Gaussian Splatting SLAM is a contemporary paper by Matsuki et al. that studies Gaussian splatting SLAM in the harder monocular setting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a914c77868426e1f8d5848af2165c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
