  <data key="d0">Splatting Paradigm</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Splatting Paradigm is a representation and modelling approach that implicitly assumes benign capture conditions and is discussed as a basis for later methods and reading threads.&lt;SEP&gt;Splatting Paradigm is the modeling assumption set behind Gaussian-splatting systems and is described as implicitly assuming benign capture conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
