<node id="Multi-View-Consistency">
  <data key="d0">Multi-View-Consistency</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-View-Consistency is a referenced question document that contains the detailed version of the open question about robustness under capture conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revising Densification">
  <data key="d0">Revising Densification</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Revising Densification is a 2024 paper by Bulo et al. that re-examines the original 3DGS recipe and argues that a more principled split criterion improves fidelity at the same primitive count.&lt;SEP&gt;Revising Densification is a 2024 paper identified as another arrival worth flagging in the sparse-view frontier discussion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Visual SLAM And MVS">
  <data key="d0">Visual SLAM And MVS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Visual SLAM And MVS is identified as one of the sub-topics covered by the weekly synthesis, grouping SLAM with multi-view reconstruction themes.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM And MVS is the sub-topic assigned to the DeepV2D paper within the input metadata.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is the sub-topic assigned to Gaussian Splatting SLAM in the input metadata.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-32b6f8bef5969e289e4fe3c770fb5f73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-06741/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Generalisation">
  <data key="d0">Generalisation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Generalisation is a major theme in the discussion of feed-forward methods that predict Gaussian parameters from sparse-view inputs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Input Image">
  <data key="d0">Input Image</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">An input image is one of the fixed inputs proposed for direct comparison between feed-forward and per-scene reconstruction methods.&lt;SEP&gt;Input Image is one of the input modalities from which LGM can generate high-resolution 3D content.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d220499711c1162411863777d237e45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/questions/inference-cost-vs-fidelity.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparse-View Frontier">
  <data key="d0">Sparse-View Frontier</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse-View Frontier is the frontier described in relation to density and generalisation for reconstruction methods using limited views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bulò Et Al.">
  <data key="d0">Bulò Et Al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Bulò Et Al. are the authors of Revising Densification, a 2024 paper that provides a corrective to the original 3DGS recipe.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Original 3DGS Recipe">
  <data key="d0">Original 3DGS Recipe</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Original 3DGS Recipe is the earlier recipe whose clone, split, and prune schedule is described as undertuned in Revising Densification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Clone / Split / Prune Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Clone / Split / Prune Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Clone / Split / Prune Schedule is the scheduling procedure in the original 3DGS recipe that is described as undertuned.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Split Criterion">
  <data key="d0">Split Criterion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Split Criterion is the criterion whose more principled treatment is said to yield meaningfully better fidelity at the same primitive count.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fidelity">
  <data key="d0">Fidelity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fidelity is the quality measure that improves when the split criterion is treated more principledly in Revising Densification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Free Gaussian Soup">
  <data key="d0">Free Gaussian Soup</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Free Gaussian Soup is the characterization used in Scaffold-GS for an unconstrained set of Gaussians that wastes capacity in low-frequency regions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Capacity">
  <data key="d0">Capacity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Capacity is the modelling resource that Scaffold-GS argues is wasted in low-frequency regions by free Gaussian soup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Frequency Regions">
  <data key="d0">Low-Frequency Regions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low-Frequency Regions are the regions in which Scaffold-GS argues free Gaussian soup wastes capacity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MVSplat">
  <data key="d0">MVSplat</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">MVSplat is a 2024 work by Chen et al. that feed-forward predicts Gaussian parameters from sparse-view inputs and removes per-scene optimisation.&lt;SEP&gt;MVSplat is a feed-forward model that predicts 3D Gaussian splatting parameters from a small set of input views in a single network pass and uses classical multi-view geometry as an inductive bias.&lt;SEP&gt;MVSplat is an example of a regression-based feed-forward reconstruction model mentioned for clean reconstruction performance.&lt;SEP&gt;MVSplat is a feed-forward Gaussian predictor named as part of the broader family that includes AGG.&lt;SEP&gt;MVSplat is a downstream method that plugs into the CUDA kernels of Gsplat.&lt;SEP&gt;MVSplat is a method identified as part of the Gaussian-prediction line of work alongside LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a36dbf1bfe982e8516ef5fb0a1dd0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-16292/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chen Et Al.">
  <data key="d0">Chen Et Al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Chen Et Al. are the authors of MVSplat, a 2024 work on feed-forward Gaussian parameter prediction from sparse-view inputs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LatentSplat">
  <data key="d0">LatentSplat</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LatentSplat is a 2024 work by Wewer et al. that feed-forward predicts Gaussian parameters from sparse-view inputs and removes per-scene optimisation.&lt;SEP&gt;LatentSplat is a generalizable 3D reconstruction method that predicts variational 3D Gaussians in a latent space to combine fast feed-forward inference with stronger extrapolation quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a36dbf1bfe982e8516ef5fb0a1dd0e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-16292/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875535</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wewer Et Al.">
  <data key="d0">Wewer Et Al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Wewer Et Al. are the authors of latentSplat, a 2024 work on feed-forward Gaussian parameter prediction from sparse-view inputs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian Parameters">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Parameters</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian Parameters are the parameters predicted by MVSplat and latentSplat from sparse-view inputs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875012</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparse-View Inputs">
  <data key="d0">Sparse-View Inputs</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse-View Inputs are the limited-view inputs from which MVSplat and latentSplat predict Gaussian parameters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a4716f0532d6b5d940a3893a269cfdc9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/weekly/2026-W17/synthesis.md</data>
