<node id="Large Reconstruction Model (LRM)">
  <data key="d0">Large Reconstruction Model (LRM)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Large Reconstruction Model (LRM) is a set of principles leveraged by TripoSR to improve the speed and quality of 3D reconstruction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/vast-ai-research-triposr/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">3D Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">3D reconstruction is the task of generating 3D models from image input and is the core capability addressed by TripoSR.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Reconstruction is the broader landscape in which DeepV2D is described as marking a transition in system design.&lt;SEP&gt;3D reconstruction is the workflow described in both SDS and SJC sections, including model execution and result export.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Reconstruction is a capability highlighted for Zero-1-to-3 and related downstream implementations.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Reconstruction is the broader area whose dominant paradigm was established by the results of Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/vast-ai-research-triposr/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876010</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NVIDIA A100 GPU">
  <data key="d0">NVIDIA A100 GPU</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">NVIDIA A100 GPU is the hardware on which TripoSR can generate high-quality 3D models in less than 0.5 seconds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bc465068a32c3c5f3d12d7446a5843df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/vast-ai-research-triposr/readme.md</data>
