  <data key="d0">DeepV2D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DeepV2D is a video-to-depth architecture that embeds classical structure-from-motion as differentiable modules inside a deep network and alternates motion and depth estimation stages to convergence at inference time.&lt;SEP&gt;DeepV2D is a learned SLAM system that is repeatedly compared against Direct Sparse Odometry and inherits a dense-photometric residual while replacing the hand-engineered front end with a recurrent network.&lt;SEP&gt;DeepV2D is a paper described as the first serious attempt at learned, differentiable bundle adjustment and as a precursor to later DROID-SLAM work.&lt;SEP&gt;DeepV2D is an earlier work by Zachary Teed and Jia Deng that introduced an iterative-refinement idea used as part of the foundation for the DROID-SLAM architecture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1234ddae6b39821bcc34ebe785c813&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-10/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876761</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zachary Teed">
  <data key="d0">Zachary Teed</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Zachary Teed is an author who introduced DeepV2D and is identified as the same first author later associated with DROID-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;Zachary Teed is a listed author of the DROID-SLAM paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Zachary Teed is a co-author of the paper and the first author whose earlier work influenced the DROID-SLAM architecture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833bec7f18854880457df56d1a16dbb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876760</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jia Deng">
  <data key="d0">Jia Deng</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jia Deng is an author who co-introduced DeepV2D.&lt;SEP&gt;Jia Deng is a listed author of the DROID-SLAM paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Jia Deng is a co-author of the paper and a collaborator on DROID-SLAM and earlier related work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833bec7f18854880457df56d1a16dbb7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876760</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Differentiable Structure From Motion">
  <data key="d0">Differentiable Structure From Motion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Differentiable Structure From Motion is the methodological pattern of unrolling geometric structure-from-motion into differentiable modules within a trainable network.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875076</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Motion Module">
  <data key="d0">Motion Module</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Motion Module is a stage in DeepV2D that estimates inter-frame camera pose using the current depth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875076</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Depth Module">
  <data key="d0">Depth Module</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Depth Module is a stage in DeepV2D that estimates per-pixel depth using the current camera pose.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875076</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bundle Adjustment">
  <data key="d0">Bundle Adjustment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Bundle Adjustment is an iterative geometric refinement procedure whose behavior DeepV2D mimics during inference.&lt;SEP&gt;Bundle adjustment is the optimization process discussed in the paper, and BARF reformulates it in a synthesis-based manner for joint scene and camera-pose optimization.&lt;SEP&gt;Bundle Adjustment is the underlying optimization concept noted as remaining conceptually the same between DROID-SLAM and DSO.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5c7f1e459e9c1753c0a4eb10eae7e1d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-30/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876123</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Epipolar Constraints">
  <data key="d0">Epipolar Constraints</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Epipolar Constraints are geometric constraints respected by the DeepV2D modules such as feature extraction, plane-sweep cost volume, and dense pose optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875076</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-View Geometry">
  <data key="d0">Multi-View Geometry</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-View Geometry is the geometric framework that DeepV2D uses and that concurrent monocular depth networks are described as ignoring.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dense Bundle Adjustment Layer">
  <data key="d0">Dense Bundle Adjustment Layer</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Dense Bundle Adjustment Layer is a component of DROID-SLAM that performs optimization over a growing keyframe graph.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Keyframe Graph">
  <data key="d0">Keyframe Graph</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Keyframe Graph is the growing graph structure over which DROID-SLAM applies its Dense Bundle Adjustment Layer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RAFT">
  <data key="d0">RAFT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">RAFT is follow-up work referenced as sharing the iterative refinement primitive associated with the DeepV2D code release.&lt;SEP&gt;RAFT is an earlier optical flow method from which the recurrent optical flow updates in DROID-SLAM descend.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a57ecf4979daf463711507fe01462548</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876676</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Learned Multi-View Stereo">
  <data key="d0">Learned Multi-View Stereo</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Learned Multi-View Stereo is a line of follow-up work for which the DeepV2D code release became a starting point.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Iterative Refinement Primitive">
  <data key="d0">Iterative Refinement Primitive</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Iterative Refinement Primitive is the repeated refinement pattern shared by DeepV2D, follow-up learned multi-view stereo work, and RAFT.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hand-Engineered MVS Pipelines">
  <data key="d0">Hand-Engineered MVS Pipelines</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Hand-Engineered MVS Pipelines are earlier multi-view stereo pipelines contrasted with learned architectures that incorporate a learned geometric solver.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Depth Estimation">
  <data key="d0">Depth Estimation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Depth Estimation is a method listed in the input metadata and is also the task performed by the depth module in DeepV2D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Feature Extraction">
  <data key="d0">Feature Extraction</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Feature Extraction is one of the modules named in the DeepV2D methodological decomposition of structure-from-motion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Plane-Sweep Cost Volume">
  <data key="d0">Plane-Sweep Cost Volume</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Plane-Sweep Cost Volume is one of the modules named in DeepV2D for unrolling the geometric structure-from-motion problem.&lt;SEP&gt;Plane-Sweep Cost Volume is the geometric mechanism built by MVSplat to capture cross-view feature similarities across discrete depth hypotheses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dense Pose Optimization">
  <data key="d0">Dense Pose Optimization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Dense Pose Optimization is one of the named modules in DeepV2D and is described as respecting epipolar constraints.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-77b518713f90adb54fa0bd6ae785bcff</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1812-04605/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875079</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Direct Sparse Odometry">
  <data key="d0">Direct Sparse Odometry</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Direct Sparse Odometry is a visual odometry system that combines a direct image-formation model with sparse keyframe windowed optimization, minimizes photometric error over pixel intensities, jointly optimizes inverse depth, camera intrinsics, and photometric calibration, and operates in real time on a single CPU.&lt;SEP&gt;Direct Sparse Odometry is a classical-geometry paper described as the last great non-learned visual odometry baseline.&lt;SEP&gt;Direct Sparse Odometry is the modern classical counterpoint to which DROID-SLAM is compared within the corpus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1234ddae6b39821bcc34ebe785c813&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-10/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jakob Engel">
  <data key="d0">Jakob Engel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jakob Engel is an author of the paper describing Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vladlen Koltun">
  <data key="d0">Vladlen Koltun</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Vladlen Koltun is an author of the paper describing Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Daniel Cremers">
  <data key="d0">Daniel Cremers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Daniel Cremers is an author of the paper describing Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LSD-SLAM">
  <data key="d0">LSD-SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LSD-SLAM is a prior direct SLAM method whose direct image-formation model is incorporated into Direct Sparse Odometry and which serves as a comparison baseline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DTAM">
  <data key="d0">DTAM</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DTAM is a dense direct method used as a contrast point for Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ORB-SLAM-Style Indirect Baselines">
  <data key="d0">ORB-SLAM-Style Indirect Baselines</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">ORB-SLAM-style indirect baselines are indirect feature-based methods used as comparison systems in the evaluation of Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TUM-monoVO Benchmark">
  <data key="d0">TUM-monoVO Benchmark</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The TUM-monoVO benchmark is one of the datasets used to evaluate Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875085</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EuRoC MAV Sequences">
  <data key="d0">EuRoC MAV Sequences</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The EuRoC MAV sequences are one of the datasets used to evaluate Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="In-House High-Frame-Rate Corpus">
  <data key="d0">In-House High-Frame-Rate Corpus</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The in-house high-frame-rate corpus is one of the datasets used to evaluate Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Photometric Calibration">
  <data key="d0">Photometric Calibration</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Photometric calibration is a calibration component covering exposure time, lens vignetting, and camera response function, and it is jointly optimized in Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Joint Windowed Bundle Adjustment">
  <data key="d0">Joint Windowed Bundle Adjustment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Joint windowed bundle adjustment is the optimization procedure used by Direct Sparse Odometry to refine pose and inverse depth simultaneously over keyframes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLM-Wiki Demo Corpus">
  <data key="d0">LLM-Wiki Demo Corpus</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The LLM-Wiki demo corpus is the collection within which Direct Sparse Odometry is positioned as a classical system.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM-Wiki Demo Corpus is described as mirroring only the README text under fair-use citation with full attribution and not redistributing code from the upstream repository.&lt;SEP&gt;The LLM-Wiki demo corpus mirrors only the README text of the upstream repository under fair-use citation with attribution and does not redistribute upstream code.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM-Wiki Demo Corpus mirrors only the repository README in order to demonstrate cross-graph linking between papers and canonical implementations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eea3b682e8bd992578c8df7af80e379d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77bbc3a5c1fbf4a8a4029857b6fa01b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876958</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SLAM-to-Radiance-Field Continuum">
  <data key="d0">SLAM-to-Radiance-Field Continuum</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The SLAM-to-radiance-field continuum is a conceptual range in which Direct Sparse Odometry is placed at the classical end, characterized by explicit residuals, sparse geometry, and real-time operation on commodity hardware.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Direct Sparse Odometry Paper">
  <data key="d0">Direct Sparse Odometry Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Direct Sparse Odometry Paper is a paper published on 2016-07-09 with arXiv identifier 1607.02565 that presents Direct Sparse Odometry.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875086</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ArXiv 1607.02565">
  <data key="d0">ArXiv 1607.02565</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ArXiv 1607.02565 is the arXiv identifier associated with Direct Sparse Odometry Paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-1607-02565/paper.md</data>
