<node id="Visual SLAM and MVS">
  <data key="d0">Visual SLAM and MVS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Visual SLAM and MVS is the subtopic under which Direct Sparse Odometry Paper is categorized.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is the sub-topic assigned to the paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is the sub-topic assigned to the NICE-SLAM paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is a subtopic covered in the digest and frames the discussion of SLAM systems and scene reconstruction methods.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is a subtopic connected to classical geometry, visual odometry, and differentiable structure-from-motion methods.&lt;SEP&gt;Visual SLAM and MVS is the sub-topic category assigned to GS-SLAM: Dense Visual SLAM with 3D Gaussian Splatting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5ec848be5aa6ee5cc0be08acd6f5935&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5c7f1e459e9c1753c0a4eb10eae7e1d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1234ddae6b39821bcc34ebe785c813&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
