<node id="Sparse Multi-View Images">
  <data key="d0">Sparse Multi-View Images</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse Multi-View Images are the small set of input views used by MVSplat to predict 3D Gaussian splatting parameters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="FeedForward">
  <data key="d0">FeedForward</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">FeedForward is the modeling paradigm used by MVSplat to perform prediction in a single network pass.&lt;SEP&gt;FeedForward is the model style used by TripoSR for single-image 3D reconstruction.&lt;SEP&gt;FeedForward is the methodological category used to describe LGM as a feed-forward 3D generator.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="pixelSplat">
  <data key="d0">pixelSplat</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">pixelSplat is a contemporaneous Gaussian predictor used as a comparison point for MVSplat in appearance quality, geometry quality, speed, parameter count, and generalisation.&lt;SEP&gt;pixelSplat is a feed-forward Gaussian predictor named as part of the broader family that includes AGG.&lt;SEP&gt;pixelSplat is a method identified as part of the Gaussian-prediction line of work alongside LGM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Classical Multi-View Geometry">
  <data key="d0">Classical Multi-View Geometry</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Classical Multi-View Geometry is an inductive bias explicitly used by MVSplat to improve localisation of predicted Gaussian centres.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cross-View Feature Similarities">
  <data key="d0">Cross-View Feature Similarities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cross-View Feature Similarities are the similarities captured in the cost volume and used by MVSplat to localise the centres of predicted Gaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Photometric Supervision">
  <data key="d0">Photometric Supervision</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Photometric Supervision is the training supervision used for MVSplat despite the model showing strong generalisation across scenes and datasets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Opacity">
  <data key="d0">Opacity</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Opacity is one of the Gaussian primitive parameters jointly predicted by MVSplat together with Gaussian centres.&lt;SEP&gt;Opacity is one of the parameter components through which exact gradient flow is documented in the supplement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876134</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Spherical-Harmonic Colour">
  <data key="d0">Spherical-Harmonic Colour</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Spherical-Harmonic Colour is one of the Gaussian primitive parameters jointly predicted by MVSplat together with Gaussian centres.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RealEstate10K">
  <data key="d0">RealEstate10K</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">RealEstate10K is a dataset on which MVSplat matches or surpasses pixelSplat in appearance and geometry quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ACID">
  <data key="d0">ACID</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ACID is a dataset on which MVSplat matches or surpasses pixelSplat in appearance and geometry quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c994414b7985eeccba7c9a66fd05d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-14627/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875111</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
