<node id="Text-to-3D">
  <data key="d0">Text-to-3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Text-to-3D is the task of generating 3D content from text prompts.&lt;SEP&gt;Text-to-3D is the generation setting referenced by DreamFusion and the optimization loop recreated in Stable-DreamFusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Text-to-3D is a method category focused on generating 3D content from text prompts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875862</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2D Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">2D Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">2D diffusion is the image-generation prior used by DreamFusion to supervise 3D optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pretrained 2D Text-to-Image Diffusion Model">
  <data key="d0">Pretrained 2D Text-to-Image Diffusion Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The pretrained 2D text-to-image diffusion model provides the prompt-conditioned image prior used by DreamFusion and is not modified by the method.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Neural Radiance Field">
  <data key="d0">Neural Radiance Field</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A Neural Radiance Field is the 3D representation initialized with random weights and iteratively refined in DreamFusion through differentiable rendering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian Perturbation">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Perturbation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian perturbation is the noise added to rendered 2D images before the diffusion model predicts a denoising direction in DreamFusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Optimization Problem">
  <data key="d0">Optimization Problem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The optimization problem is the formulation DreamFusion uses to replace the need for a large-scale ground-truth 3D corpus by optimizing against an existing image prior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2D Image Prior">
  <data key="d0">2D Image Prior</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2D image prior is the prompt-conditioned visual prior from the diffusion model that supervises 3D optimization in DreamFusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fantasia3D">
  <data key="d0">Fantasia3D</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Fantasia3D is a later work in the text-to-3D literature presented as following DreamFusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Co-SLAM: Joint Coordinate and Sparse Parametric Encodings for Neural Real-Time SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Co-SLAM: Joint Coordinate and Sparse Parametric Encodings for Neural Real-Time SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Co-SLAM: Joint Coordinate and Sparse Parametric Encodings for Neural Real-Time SLAM is a paper published on 2023-04-27 that presents the Co-SLAM system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
