  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hybrid Scene Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Hybrid Scene Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hybrid Scene Encoding is the scene representation in Co-SLAM that combines a multi-resolution hash grid with a coordinate-based one-blob encoding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-Resolution Hash Grid">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Resolution Hash Grid</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-Resolution Hash Grid is a component of the Co-SLAM scene encoding that contributes fast convergence and high-frequency detail.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coordinate-Based One-Blob Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Coordinate-Based One-Blob Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Coordinate-Based One-Blob Encoding is a component of the Co-SLAM scene encoding that encourages surface coherence in unobserved regions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Variational SDS">
  <data key="d0">Variational SDS</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Variational SDS is a refinement of Score Distillation Sampling described as part of later work on lower-variance estimators.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stable-DreamFusion">
  <data key="d0">Stable-DreamFusion</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Stable-DreamFusion is the open-source repository associated with DreamFusion and is identified as ashawkey/stable-dreamfusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2209.14988">
  <data key="d0">2209.14988</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">2209.14988 is the arXiv identifier listed for DreamFusion in the metadata.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Shallow MLP">
  <data key="d0">Shallow MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Shallow MLP is the prediction module in Co-SLAM that outputs signed distance and colour for queried 3D points.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Camera Tracking">
  <data key="d0">Camera Tracking</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Camera Tracking is performed in Co-SLAM by inverting rendering through photometric and depth loss.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Depth Loss">
  <data key="d0">Depth Loss</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Depth Loss is used in Co-SLAM to support rendering-based camera tracking.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Global BundleAdjustment">
  <data key="d0">Global BundleAdjustment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Global BundleAdjustment is the optimisation strategy in Co-SLAM that folds tracking and mapping over all keyframes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ray Sampling Strategy">
  <data key="d0">Ray Sampling Strategy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Ray Sampling Strategy is a sampling approach in Co-SLAM that keeps bundle adjustment tractable at interactive rates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875233</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ScanNet">
  <data key="d0">ScanNet</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ScanNet is a dataset used to evaluate Co-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;ScanNet is a dataset used in experiments evaluating the tracking accuracy and rendering quality of Point-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;ScanNet is one of the challenging datasets on which NICE-SLAM is evaluated.&lt;SEP&gt;ScanNet is a benchmark dataset on which MonoSDF is reported to substantially improve over prior methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a914c77868426e1f8d5848af2165c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-04278/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-12130/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="iMAP">
  <data key="d0">iMAP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">iMAP is a prior neural SLAM method that uses a small active-keyframe window for optimisation.&lt;SEP&gt;iMAP is a prior dense neural SLAM method that uses a fixed-resolution grid encoding and is referenced as a memory comparison point for Point-SLAM.&lt;SEP&gt;iMAP is described as the first neural-implicit SLAM system and as the baseline whose single shared scene-wide MLP causes scaling, over-smoothing, and forgetting problems that NICE-SLAM addresses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a914c77868426e1f8d5848af2165c17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dea341f1a2c850107557c2c2de09ba69</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-04278/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-12130/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875625</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GaussianSplatting-Based Variants">
  <data key="d0">GaussianSplatting-Based Variants</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">GaussianSplatting-Based Variants are a later wave of neural SLAM systems that followed Co-SLAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hybrid Implicit Representations">
  <data key="d0">Hybrid Implicit Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hybrid Implicit Representations are representation approaches for which Co-SLAM remains a strong baseline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Surface-Completion Priors">
  <data key="d0">Surface-Completion Priors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Surface-Completion Priors are priors studied through Co-SLAM for their interaction with high-frequency parametric encodings in incremental reconstruction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Frequency Parametric Encodings">
  <data key="d0">High-Frequency Parametric Encodings</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Frequency Parametric Encodings are encoding components that provide detail and are studied in relation to surface-completion priors in Co-SLAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Incremental Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Incremental Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Incremental Reconstruction is the reconstruction setting in which the interaction between surface-completion priors and high-frequency parametric encodings is studied.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="StructureFromMotion">
  <data key="d0">StructureFromMotion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">StructureFromMotion is a method listed for the paper as part of its methodological context.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BundleAdjustment">
  <data key="d0">BundleAdjustment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">BundleAdjustment is a method listed for the paper and is the optimisation family extended in Co-SLAM through a global formulation over keyframes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tracking Accuracy">
  <data key="d0">Tracking Accuracy</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Tracking Accuracy is an evaluation measure on which Co-SLAM matches or exceeds prior neural SLAM methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0baf845c234eac590adb7912cde85960</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2304-14377/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Keunhong Park">
  <data key="d0">Keunhong Park</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Keunhong Park is an author of HyperNeRF.&lt;SEP&gt;Keunhong Park is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Utkarsh Sinha">
  <data key="d0">Utkarsh Sinha</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Utkarsh Sinha is an author of HyperNeRF.&lt;SEP&gt;Utkarsh Sinha is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sofien Bouaziz">
  <data key="d0">Sofien Bouaziz</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Sofien Bouaziz is an author of HyperNeRF.&lt;SEP&gt;Sofien Bouaziz is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dan B Goldman">
  <data key="d0">Dan B Goldman</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dan B Goldman is an author of HyperNeRF.&lt;SEP&gt;Dan B Goldman is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Steven M. Seitz">
  <data key="d0">Steven M. Seitz</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Steven M. Seitz is an author of HyperNeRF.&lt;SEP&gt;Steven M. Seitz is an author of Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Topological Change">
  <data key="d0">Topological Change</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Topological change is a scene property involving discontinuities such as an opening mouth, an unclenching fist, or a knife slicing fruit, which cannot be represented by a continuous deformation field.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deformation Field">
  <data key="d0">Deformation Field</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The deformation field is a mechanism that warps observed points into canonical 3D coordinates and is retained in HyperNeRF from Nerfies.&lt;SEP&gt;Deformation Field is a method category listed in the paper metadata and is the core mechanism used by Nerfies to model non-rigid motion.&lt;SEP&gt;Deformation Field is the component in 4D-GS that models how canonical Gaussians deform over time.&lt;SEP&gt;Deformation Field is a motion-encoding mechanism that maps each timestamp back to canonical coordinates in prior dynamic formulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb7662ca60286f5c929b6bb92d667dfd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-393d4b1d50fb3d20d718f84708cec66c</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2310-08528/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-03307/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876985</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Higher-Dimensional Ambient Space">
  <data key="d0">Higher-Dimensional Ambient Space</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The higher-dimensional ambient space is the expanded canonical space used by HyperNeRF to resolve discontinuities caused by topological change.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ambient Coordinate">
  <data key="d0">Ambient Coordinate</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The ambient coordinate is the per-frame value that locates each input frame within the higher-dimensional ambient space for slicing the radiance field.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Level-Set Methods">
  <data key="d0">Level-Set Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Level-set methods are classical geometry methods that inspire HyperNeRF's construction of evolving surfaces as slices of a higher-dimensional implicit function.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Classical Geometry">
  <data key="d0">Classical Geometry</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Classical geometry is the field from which the level-set-method inspiration for HyperNeRF is drawn.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Benchmark of Casually Captured Topology-Changing Clips">
  <data key="d0">Benchmark of Casually Captured Topology-Changing Clips</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The benchmark of casually captured topology-changing clips is the evaluation dataset on which HyperNeRF is compared against Nerfies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Moment-Interpolation">
  <data key="d0">Moment-Interpolation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Moment-interpolation is an evaluation setting in which HyperNeRF reduces LPIPS error compared to Nerfies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Novel-View Synthesis">
  <data key="d0">Novel-View Synthesis</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Novel-view synthesis is a rendering task and evaluation setting in which HyperNeRF reduces LPIPS error compared to Nerfies.&lt;SEP&gt;Novel-view synthesis is the rendering task discussed in the paper, with the proposed approach targeting high-quality real-time results at 1080p resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;Novel-View Synthesis is the task targeted by 3D Gaussian Splatting and related follow-on methods discussed in the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876013</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic-3D Portion of the Corpus">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic-3D Portion of the Corpus</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The dynamic-3D portion of the corpus is the part of the mapped corpus in which both Nerfies and HyperNeRF appear together.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Elastic Regularization">
  <data key="d0">Elastic Regularization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Elastic regularization is a reused component from Nerfies that is retained in HyperNeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coarse-To-Fine Positional Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Coarse-To-Fine Positional Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Coarse-to-fine positional encoding is a reused component from Nerfies that is retained in HyperNeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875352</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Dynamic Methods">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Dynamic Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular dynamic methods are subsequent methods that adopted HyperNeRF's higher-dimensional canonical-space construction to address topology-related difficulties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875352</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deformable Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">Deformable Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Deformable radiance fields are the class of radiance-field models for nonrigid scenes, for which the Nerfies and HyperNeRF pair is described as a canonical pre-Gaussian reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e871ba692ecdc2269f6f148bf3849940</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-13228/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875352</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Magic123 Paper">
  <data key="d0">Magic123 Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Magic123 Paper is a 2023 research paper titled "Magic123: One Image to High-Quality 3D Object Generation Using Both 2D and 3D Diffusion Priors" that presents the Magic123 method and its evaluation context.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
