<node id="ImageTo3D">
  <data key="d0">ImageTo3D</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">ImageTo3D is the task setting in which a 3D object representation is generated from image input, and it is the category of pipeline used by Magic123.&lt;SEP&gt;ImageTo3D is a class of systems for converting images into 3D representations and is the broader method category to which LRM belongs.&lt;SEP&gt;ImageTo3D is the task and method category in which AGG maps a single image to a 3D representation.&lt;SEP&gt;ImageTo3D is a method listed for Zero-1-to-3 and refers to generating 3D structure from image input.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Differentiable Mesh Representation">
  <data key="d0">Differentiable Mesh Representation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Differentiable Mesh Representation is the memory-efficient representation used in the second stage of Magic123 to optimize a higher-resolution textured surface.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2D Text-to-Image Prior">
  <data key="d0">2D Text-to-Image Prior</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">2D Text-to-Image Prior is the diffusion prior in Magic123 that contributes stylistic richness and detailed appearance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D-Aware Diffusion Prior">
  <data key="d0">3D-Aware Diffusion Prior</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">3D-Aware Diffusion Prior is the diffusion prior in Magic123 that promotes geometric consistency across novel views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Textual Inversion">
  <data key="d0">Textual Inversion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Textual Inversion is the method used in Magic123 to capture the identity of the reference image in a reusable token for diffusion guidance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DepthEstimation">
  <data key="d0">DepthEstimation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DepthEstimation is used in Magic123 as a monocular regularizer to prevent degenerate flat or hollow radiance field solutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single Unposed Photograph">
  <data key="d0">Single Unposed Photograph</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Single Unposed Photograph is the sole input image type from which Magic123 reconstructs a textured 3D object.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Textured 3D Mesh">
  <data key="d0">Textured 3D Mesh</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Textured 3D Mesh is the 3D output recovered by Magic123 from a single input photograph.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single-Image 3D Generation">
  <data key="d0">Single-Image 3D Generation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Single-Image 3D Generation is the broader research area to which Magic123 contributes and within which it became a reference point.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Optimization-Based Pipelines">
  <data key="d0">Optimization-Based Pipelines</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Optimization-Based Pipelines are high-fidelity 3D generation approaches that continue to be informed by Magic123's coarse-to-fine recipe and multi-prior design.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Code">
  <data key="d0">Code</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Code is one of the released artifacts that accompanies the Magic123 Paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Code is the upstream repository content that the corpus explicitly omits for NVlabs/instant-ngp.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ce2165eaaf1422a9b02235e41e20e20</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876671</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Models">
  <data key="d0">Models</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Models are released artifacts that accompany the Magic123 Paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Generated Assets">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Generated Assets</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Generated Assets are released artifacts that accompany the Magic123 Paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="In-The-Wild Image Inputs">
  <data key="d0">In-The-Wild Image Inputs</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">In-The-Wild Image Inputs are real image inputs identified by the Magic123 Paper as the appropriate evaluation regime for single-image 3D generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875372</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ShapeNet Renders">
  <data key="d0">ShapeNet Renders</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ShapeNet Renders are synthetic rendered inputs contrasted with in-the-wild image inputs in the evaluation discussion of the Magic123 Paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875373</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scalar Trade-Off Parameter">
  <data key="d0">Scalar Trade-Off Parameter</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Scalar Trade-Off Parameter is the single control variable in Magic123 that modulates the balance between the 2D prior and the 3D-aware diffusion prior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875373</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Reference-View Supervision">
  <data key="d0">Reference-View Supervision</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Reference-View Supervision is the supervision signal used in the first stage of Magic123 during neural radiance field optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875373</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Novel-View Guidance">
  <data key="d0">Novel-View Guidance</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Novel-View Guidance is the guidance mechanism used in the first stage of Magic123 to support generation beyond the reference view.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11ccc947afd3d6b02019a4d324bd68d3</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2306-17843/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875373</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object">
  <data key="d0">Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object is the cited 2023 work described in the bibliography entry.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object is a zero-shot image-to-3D method and project presented with links to a project page, paper, weights, and live demo.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object is an acknowledged research work on zero-shot conversion from one image to a 3D object.&lt;SEP&gt;Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object is the work officially released by the repository and is associated with Liu et al., 2023.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cab660adb0c0033bdf9b7cb3ec02bfd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b96bffec912e64ed752226976c3822&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc</data>
