<node id="VRAM">
  <data key="d0">VRAM</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">VRAM is the GPU memory resource discussed as a limiting factor for running the app and for training on multi-GPU systems.&lt;SEP&gt;VRAM is the memory resource required by the demo, with the code base described as running at around 22 GB VRAM.&lt;SEP&gt;VRAM is the memory resource whose consumption can be reduced by storing source image data on the CPU.&lt;SEP&gt;VRAM is video memory, with 4 GB recommended for the viewing setup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d057f3bc5fa56c4a6477fe9f9195f8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eadedf8ea91fdbae049617371c868a2e</data>
