  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GPU">
  <data key="d0">GPU</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A GPU is the hardware used to run the app, training, and reconstruction workflows described in the text.&lt;SEP&gt;GPU is the hardware platform on which the authors implement perspective-correct rasterisation efficiently.&lt;SEP&gt;GPU is the required hardware for running DROID-SLAM inference, demos, training, and some evaluation workloads, with different memory requirements described in the README.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833bec7f18854880457df56d1a16dbb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/princeton-vl-droid-slam/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876658</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Image-Conditioned Stable Diffusion Checkpoint">
  <data key="d0">Image-Conditioned Stable Diffusion Checkpoint</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The image-conditioned stable diffusion checkpoint is a downloadable model checkpoint used to finetune the training setup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="valid_paths.json">
  <data key="d0">valid_paths.json</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">valid_paths.json is a file that must be downloaded, unzipped, and moved under the view_release folder for the workflow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paper">
  <data key="d0">Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The paper is cited as the source discussing the importance of large batch size and the train and validation split used by the authors.&lt;SEP&gt;Paper is the referenced publication whose reported metrics differ from metrics produced by the current codebase when evaluating the pre-trained models.&lt;SEP&gt;The paper is a linked resource for Instant Neural Graphics Primitives with a Multiresolution Hash Encoding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ace087a61df1fdd6d045f0f39a3166c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eea3b682e8bd992578c8df7af80e379d</data>
