<node id="Elevation Angle">
  <data key="d0">Elevation Angle</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The elevation angle is a recommended input estimate describing the camera viewpoint of an image, with example values for top, front, and bottom views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Extrinsics Matrix">
  <data key="d0">Extrinsics Matrix</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The extrinsics matrix is the place where the elevation angle is currently hard-coded in transforms_train.json.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="transforms_train.json">
  <data key="d0">transforms_train.json</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">transforms_train.json is the file containing the hard-coded extrinsics matrix used for viewpoint information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ubuntu 20.04">
  <data key="d0">Ubuntu 20.04</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Ubuntu 20.04 is the operating system version on which the installation processes were tested.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NVIDIA">
  <data key="d0">NVIDIA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">NVIDIA is the organization associated with the GPU used in the tested installation system.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is listed as one of the institutes from which project contributors come.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is the organization referenced through the upstream license name and the research licensing form for business inquiries.&lt;SEP&gt;NVIDIA is the organization that provides the reference implementation and the upstream license for NVlabs/instant-ngp.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb5c9e689ffa78ae20907ec96c23e19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eea3b682e8bd992578c8df7af80e379d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ce2165eaaf1422a9b02235e41e20e20</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876670</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ampere Architecture">
  <data key="d0">Ampere Architecture</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Ampere architecture is the GPU architecture of the NVIDIA GPU used in the tested installation setup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Janus Problem">
  <data key="d0">Janus Problem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Janus problem is a viewpoint-related ambiguity problem that the method is said to fundamentally alleviate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Camera Perspective">
  <data key="d0">Camera Perspective</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Camera perspective is modeled explicitly by the method to reduce ambiguity and viewpoint bias.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Synthetic Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Synthetic Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The synthetic dataset is described as large-scale and high-quality, providing ground truth needed to reduce ambiguity and bias.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Text-To-Image Model">
  <data key="d0">Text-To-Image Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A text-to-image model is described as containing viewpoint ambiguity and bias that the method alleviates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zero-1-to-3 Models">
  <data key="d0">Zero-1-to-3 Models</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Zero-1-to-3 models explicitly model viewpoint changes and are finetuned on Objaverse to preserve consistency and viewpoint accuracy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SJC">
  <data key="d0">SJC</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">SJC is a referenced repository and reconstruction approach acknowledged as a basis for the repository.&lt;SEP&gt;SJC is a publicly released codebase or project acknowledged both for its released code and for helpful feedback from its authors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cab660adb0c0033bdf9b7cb3ec02bfd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRDi">
  <data key="d0">NeRDi</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRDi is a referenced work whose authors are acknowledged for publicly releasing their code.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRDi is a referenced work whose authors are thanked for providing helpful feedback.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4cab660adb0c0033bdf9b7cb3ec02bfd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Repository">
  <data key="d0">The Repository</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The repository contains the training, dataset, and 3D reconstruction workflows described in the text and is acknowledged as being based on other released projects and resources.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d7c1d8ea46e8d39c693dee7fccbb8f2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Creative Commons License">
  <data key="d0">Creative Commons License</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Creative Commons license refers to the original per-object licensing in Objaverse that also applies to individual object renderings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d1cb4f77562fea889c9e32a8c9b6b118</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
