<node id="Ashawkey/Stable-DreamFusion">
  <data key="d0">Ashawkey/Stable-DreamFusion</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Ashawkey/Stable-DreamFusion is a widely used open reimplementation repository of DreamFusion: Text-to-3D using 2D Diffusion created by Jiaxiang Tang and built on Stable Diffusion rather than Google's closed Imagen model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DreamFusion: Text-to-3D Using 2D Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">DreamFusion: Text-to-3D Using 2D Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">DreamFusion: Text-to-3D Using 2D Diffusion is the original work that Stable-DreamFusion reimplements and that was authored by Poole et al. in 2022.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion: Text-to-3D Using 2D Diffusion is an acknowledged research work on text-to-3D generation using 2D diffusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b96bffec912e64ed752226976c3822</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Poole Et Al.">
  <data key="d0">Poole Et Al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Poole Et Al. are the authors credited in the text for DreamFusion: Text-to-3D Using 2D Diffusion in 2022.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Google">
  <data key="d0">Google</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Google is the organization associated with the closed Imagen diffusion model used by the original DreamFusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875484</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF/DMTet">
  <data key="d0">NeRF/DMTet</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF/DMTet is a hash-grid backed geometry representation provided in Stable-DreamFusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875486</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="arxiv-2209-14988">
  <data key="d0">arxiv-2209-14988</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">arxiv-2209-14988 is the canonical paper identifier associated with the repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f98a94c0a3f79ba956d93735db4362c0</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875486</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparse 3D Voxel Grid">
  <data key="d0">Sparse 3D Voxel Grid</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse 3D Voxel Grid is the explicit scene representation used by Plenoxels, storing values only at occupied voxels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Spherical-Harmonic Coefficients">
  <data key="d0">Spherical-Harmonic Coefficients</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Spherical-Harmonic Coefficients are stored in occupied voxels to describe view-dependent color in the Plenoxels representation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emission-Absorption Volume Rendering Integral">
  <data key="d0">Emission-Absorption Volume Rendering Integral</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Emission-Absorption Volume Rendering Integral is the rendering procedure used by both Plenoxels and NeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trilinear Interpolation">
  <data key="d0">Trilinear Interpolation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Trilinear Interpolation is the procedure used by Plenoxels to query density and color values from the voxel grid.&lt;SEP&gt;Trilinear Interpolation is one of the operations supported by the CUDA kernels in the repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Total-Variation Priors">
  <data key="d0">Total-Variation Priors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Total-Variation Priors are explicit regularization terms applied to voxel values in Plenoxels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparsity Priors">
  <data key="d0">Sparsity Priors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparsity Priors are explicit regularization terms applied to voxel values in Plenoxels to encourage sparse occupancy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Grid-Based Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">Grid-Based Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Grid-Based Radiance Fields is the methodological category for which Plenoxels is described as the canonical reference within the corpus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Explicit Representations">
  <data key="d0">Explicit Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Explicit Representations are scene representations argued by the paper to deserve a first-class place in radiance field methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coordinate-Based MLPs">
  <data key="d0">Coordinate-Based MLPs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Coordinate-Based MLPs are implicit neural scene representations presented as the alternative class alongside which explicit representations should stand.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scalar Density">
  <data key="d0">Scalar Density</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Scalar Density is the per-voxel value stored in the Plenoxels representation to model scene density for rendering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Voxel Coefficients">
  <data key="d0">Voxel Coefficients</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Voxel Coefficients are the directly optimized values in Plenoxels, trained against photometric loss.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Standard NeRF Synthetic and Forward-Facing Benchmarks">
  <data key="d0">Standard NeRF Synthetic and Forward-Facing Benchmarks</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Standard NeRF Synthetic and Forward-Facing Benchmarks are the evaluation benchmarks on which Plenoxels matches NeRF on PSNR, SSIM, and LPIPS.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implicit Representations">
  <data key="d0">Implicit Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Implicit Representations are scene representations discussed as having been conflated with volume rendering in early NeRF literature.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering">
  <data key="d0">3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering is a paper describing a method for high-quality real-time novel-view synthesis using 3D Gaussians, interleaved optimization and density control, and a visibility-aware rendering algorithm.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering is a paper published on 2023-08-08 that presents a primitive-based representation for real-time radiance field rendering and novel-view synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering is the canonical paper associated with the repository and provides the context for the implementation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77bbc3a5c1fbf4a8a4029857b6fa01b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876956</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
