<node id="Gaussian-Splatting License">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian-Splatting License</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian-Splatting License is the research-only, non-commercial license named in the mirrored README as the license governing the upstream repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Radiance Field Methods">
  <data key="d0">Radiance Field Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Radiance Field Methods are described as approaches that revolutionized novel-view synthesis of scenes captured with multiple photos or videos but often require costly neural networks or trade speed for quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparse Points">
  <data key="d0">Sparse Points</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse points are the starting data produced during camera calibration from which the method represents the scene with 3D Gaussians.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Camera Calibration">
  <data key="d0">Camera Calibration</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Camera calibration is the process that produces the sparse points used to initialize the scene representation in the paper's method.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Interleaved Optimization and Density Control">
  <data key="d0">Interleaved Optimization and Density Control</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Interleaved optimization and density control is one of the paper's key elements, applied to 3D Gaussians during scene optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Visibility-Aware Rendering Algorithm">
  <data key="d0">Visibility-Aware Rendering Algorithm</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Visibility-aware rendering algorithm is the fast rendering method developed in the paper to support anisotropic splatting, accelerate training, and allow real-time rendering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anisotropic Splatting">
  <data key="d0">Anisotropic Splatting</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Anisotropic splatting is a rendering capability supported by the visibility-aware rendering algorithm described in the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ACM Transactions on Graphics">
  <data key="d0">ACM Transactions on Graphics</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">ACM Transactions on Graphics is the journal listed in the BibTeX entry for the paper 3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering.&lt;SEP&gt;ACM Transactions on Graphics is the publication venue listed for the Instant-NGP paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-41e2a18164d88d58975577aab63d7325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eea3b682e8bd992578c8df7af80e379d</data>
