  <data key="d2">FAQ is a referenced source that contains a workaround for Windows submodule build problems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Optimizer">
  <data key="d0">Optimizer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Optimizer is the training procedure that is run with the `python train.py -s &lt;path&gt;` command.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MipNeRF360">
  <data key="d0">MipNeRF360</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">MipNeRF360 is a referenced method whose training and test split style is used for evaluation.&lt;SEP&gt;MipNeRF360 is a referenced work whose image resolution target and evaluation split style are followed by the described system.&lt;SEP&gt;MipNeRF360 is a source dataset path required by the evaluation script if training or rendering is performed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eadedf8ea91fdbae049617371c868a2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ace087a61df1fdd6d045f0f39a3166c</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Source Image Data">
  <data key="d0">Source Image Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Source Image Data is the loaded image input that can be placed on different devices during training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CPU">
  <data key="d0">CPU</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CPU is a recommended device for source image data when training on large or high-resolution datasets to reduce VRAM consumption.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HrsPythonix">
  <data key="d0">HrsPythonix</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">HrsPythonix is a credited contributor associated with the recommendation about using the CPU for source image data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Spherical Harmonics">
  <data key="d0">Spherical Harmonics</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Spherical Harmonics is a representation whose order is configurable and whose forward and backward computation can be performed with PyTorch.&lt;SEP&gt;Spherical harmonics are the mechanism through which colour is represented among the appearance attributes predicted by AGG.&lt;SEP&gt;Spherical Harmonics is the encoding used for the view-dependent colour carried by each Gaussian.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876014</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Covariance">
  <data key="d0">3D Covariance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">3D Covariance is a quantity in the pipeline whose forward and backward computation can be performed with PyTorch.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Debug Mode">
  <data key="d0">Debug Mode</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Debug Mode is an execution mode that can be enabled to diagnose errors and can create a dump file if the rasterizer fails.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dump File">
  <data key="d0">Dump File</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Dump File is a file created when the rasterizer fails in debug mode and can be forwarded in an issue for inspection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Issue">
  <data key="d0">Issue</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Issue is the reporting channel to which a dump file may be forwarded for investigation.&lt;SEP&gt;An Issue is a support request that can be opened to ask for help if other resources do not resolve the problem.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d77e66aa7cc152f532934b3e4405857</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876505</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GUI Server">
  <data key="d0">GUI Server</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">GUI Server is the server started by the training script and configured with an IP address and port.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian Model">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Model</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian Model is the model saved by the training script at specified save iterations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f03bfcd22d34d1827ec44d4dfcce42df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/graphdeco-inria-gaussian-splatting/readme.md</data>
