</node>
<node id="Neural Implicit Surface Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Neural Implicit Surface Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Neural implicit surface reconstruction is the reconstruction task addressed by MonoSDF using monocular geometric cues and neural implicit representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Geometric Cues">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Geometric Cues</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular geometric cues are the two single-image supervision signals used by MonoSDF to strengthen reconstruction in regions with weak photometric constraints.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Depth Predictor">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Depth Predictor</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A monocular depth predictor is used in MonoSDF to produce per-pixel relative depth estimates for supervision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Surface-Normal Predictor">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Surface-Normal Predictor</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A monocular surface-normal predictor is used in MonoSDF to produce per-pixel normal estimates for supervision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scale-And-Shift-Invariant Depth-Consistency Loss">
  <data key="d0">Scale-And-Shift-Invariant Depth-Consistency Loss</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The scale-and-shift-invariant depth-consistency loss compares predicted relative depth with rendered SDF depth in MonoSDF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Signed-Distance Function">
  <data key="d0">Signed-Distance Function</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The signed-distance function is the surface representation backbone used in the MonoSDF pipeline and provides analytic gradients for rendered normals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monolithic MLPs">
  <data key="d0">Monolithic MLPs</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Monolithic MLPs are one of the representation backbones evaluated in the MonoSDF study.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single-Resolution Voxel Grids">
  <data key="d0">Single-Resolution Voxel Grids</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Single-resolution voxel grids are one of the representation backbones evaluated in the MonoSDF study.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-Resolution Hash Grids">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Resolution Hash Grids</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-resolution hash grids are a representation choice studied in MonoSDF and are reported as giving the best speed-quality trade-off.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tanks-And-Temples">
  <data key="d0">Tanks-And-Temples</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Tanks-And-Temples is a benchmark dataset on which MonoSDF is reported to substantially improve over prior methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875633</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MultiViewStereo">
  <data key="d0">MultiViewStereo</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">MultiViewStereo is a method tag associated with MonoSDF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Photometric RGB Loss">
  <data key="d0">Photometric RGB Loss</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Photometric RGB loss is the image-based supervision term described as being too weak on its own in regions with low texture or low multi-view overlap.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hash-Grid Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Hash-Grid Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Hash-grid encoding is part of the recipe crystallized by MonoSDF for effective surface reconstruction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Priors">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Priors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular priors are the monocular geometric cues incorporated into the MonoSDF recipe for dense supervision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
