  <data key="d0">Nvidia-Docker</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Nvidia-Docker is an alternative suggested for headless server usage when OpenGL initialization problems occur.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Custom Stable-Diffusion Checkpoint">
  <data key="d0">Custom Stable-Diffusion Checkpoint</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Custom Stable-Diffusion Checkpoint is a Hugging Face-hosted checkpoint that can be supplied through `--hf_key`.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CUDA Extensions">
  <data key="d0">CUDA Extensions</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CUDA Extensions are compiled components required for the default Instant-NGP workflow and may take time to build on first run.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Raymarching">
  <data key="d0">Raymarching</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Raymarching is an extension module that can be installed manually into the Python path as part of the project setup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gridencoder">
  <data key="d0">Gridencoder</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Gridencoder is an extension module that may need to be re-installed when CUDA source updates cause incompatible function argument errors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Negative Text Prompt">
  <data key="d0">Negative Text Prompt</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Negative Text Prompt is a prompt feature that allows exclusion of specified visual attributes, such as removing the color red from a generated rose.&lt;SEP&gt;Negative Text Prompt is a prompting method supported in training that allows undesired attributes to be specified separately from the main text prompt.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0ea2d1fff273acbdf62338200407400&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Preprocess_Image.py">
  <data key="d0">Preprocess_Image.py</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Preprocess_Image.py is a preprocessing script that prepares an input image and exports RGBA, depth, and normal image files for image-conditioned 3D generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vanilla NeRF Backbone">
  <data key="d0">Vanilla NeRF Backbone</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Vanilla NeRF Backbone is a pure PyTorch NeRF implementation that avoids building extensions but has slower rendering speed and higher GPU memory usage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DMTet Finetuning">
  <data key="d0">DMTet Finetuning</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DMTet Finetuning is a higher-resolution mesh finetuning method that uses the `--dmtet` option and can be initialized from a NeRF checkpoint or a mesh.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zero-1-to-3 Backend">
  <data key="d0">Zero-1-to-3 Backend</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Zero-1-to-3 Backend is the backend enabled by providing a processed image without a text prompt for image-to-3D training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stable-Diffusion Backend">
  <data key="d0">Stable-Diffusion Backend</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Stable-Diffusion Backend is the backend enabled when both text and image inputs are provided for 3D generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Depth Estimation">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Depth Estimation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular Depth Estimation is an auxiliary method used by default to support image-to-3D generation, though it can be disabled if inaccurate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cubvh">
  <data key="d0">Cubvh</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Cubvh is an installable dependency required when initializing DMTet with a mesh to generate texture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mesh">
  <data key="d0">Mesh</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Mesh is a 3D output artifact that can be saved or used to initialize DMTet, and may include OBJ, MTL, and PNG texture files.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GUI">
  <data key="d0">GUI</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">GUI is an interactive visualization interface used for free view control during testing, including visualization of DMTet results.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GPU Memory">
  <data key="d0">GPU Memory</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">GPU Memory is a hardware resource referenced as a requirement for running the workspace trial configuration and as a constraint for Vanilla NeRF training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875661</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="main.py">
  <data key="d0">main.py</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">main.py is the primary script used to train, test, visualize, and export outputs for text-conditioned, image-conditioned, and mesh-related 3D generation workflows.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6fbd6ef7fa46c0ba5c1daac3eb1cafc5</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/ashawkey-stable-dreamfusion/readme.md</data>
