  <data key="d5">1778875719</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Feng Liu">
  <data key="d0">Feng Liu</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Feng Liu is an author of LRM: Large Reconstruction Model for Single Image to 3D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kalyan Sunkavalli">
  <data key="d0">Kalyan Sunkavalli</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Kalyan Sunkavalli is an author of LRM: Large Reconstruction Model for Single Image to 3D.&lt;SEP&gt;Kalyan Sunkavalli is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875862</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trung Bui">
  <data key="d0">Trung Bui</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Trung Bui is an author of LRM: Large Reconstruction Model for Single Image to 3D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hao Tan">
  <data key="d0">Hao Tan</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Hao Tan is an author of LRM: Large Reconstruction Model for Single Image to 3D.&lt;SEP&gt;Hao Tan is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single-Image 3D Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Single-Image 3D Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Single-image 3D reconstruction is the task of reconstructing 3D structure from one input image and is the main problem addressed by the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TransformerArchitecture">
  <data key="d0">TransformerArchitecture</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">TransformerArchitecture is the deep cross-attention transformer design used within LRM to predict a triplane representation from encoder features.&lt;SEP&gt;TransformerArchitecture is the model architecture used by the sparse-view reconstructor in Instant3D.&lt;SEP&gt;TransformerArchitecture is the architectural approach introduced by LargeReconstructionModel and used by TripoSR.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ShapeNet">
  <data key="d0">ShapeNet</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ShapeNet is a small dataset used by earlier per-category reconstruction systems as a contrast to the broader training setup of LRM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MVImgNet">
  <data key="d0">MVImgNet</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">MVImgNet is a dataset providing real captures that are combined with Objaverse data to train LRM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Amortised Inference">
  <data key="d0">Amortised Inference</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Amortised inference is the research direction toward which the paper is credited with shifting 3D reconstruction, moving away from per-scene optimisation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875722</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Foundation-Model Scaling Laws">
  <data key="d0">Foundation-Model Scaling Laws</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Foundation-model scaling laws are the scaling principles that the paper applies directly to single-image 3D reconstruction through the Large Reconstruction Model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875722</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-View Supervision">
  <data key="d0">Multi-View Supervision</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-view supervision is the end-to-end training setup used to train the Large Reconstruction Model on roughly one million objects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875722</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-View Gaussian Representation">
  <data key="d0">Multi-View Gaussian Representation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-view Gaussian representation is the representation used by LGM in place of the implicit radiance field in the Large Reconstruction Model family.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-faebadc81c39822f071629969e8b6a2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-04400/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875722</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields is a 2021 paper that proposes joint optimization of neural scene representation and camera poses to enable pose-free NeRF training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wei-Chiu Ma">
  <data key="d0">Wei-Chiu Ma</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Wei-Chiu Ma is an author of BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Antonio Torralba">
  <data key="d0">Antonio Torralba</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Antonio Torralba is an author of BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Simon Lucey">
  <data key="d0">Simon Lucey</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Simon Lucey is an author of BARF: Bundle-Adjusting Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Structure-from-Motion Pipeline">
  <data key="d0">Structure-from-Motion Pipeline</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A structure-from-motion pipeline is an upstream process used to provide accurate camera poses for NeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Synthesis-Based Bundle Adjustment">
  <data key="d0">Synthesis-Based Bundle Adjustment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Synthesis-based bundle adjustment is the formulation used by BARF to jointly optimize scene representation and camera poses in one gradient-descent loop.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875731</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Classical Image Alignment">
  <data key="d0">Classical Image Alignment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Classical image alignment is a framework to which the paper draws a theoretical link by relating NeRF pixel synthesis and observation matching to photometric alignment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Photometric Residual">
  <data key="d0">Photometric Residual</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Photometric residual is the first-order alignment quantity used to explain the connection between NeRF pixel matching and classical image alignment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lucas-Kanade Alignment">
  <data key="d0">Lucas-Kanade Alignment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Lucas-Kanade alignment is a classical coarse-to-fine image alignment method cited as a source of robustness wisdom.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Frequency Sinusoidal Positional Encoding">
  <data key="d0">High-Frequency Sinusoidal Positional Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">High-frequency sinusoidal positional encoding is a NeRF encoding component that makes the camera-pose gradient landscape spiky and prone to local minima.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coarse-to-Fine Annealing Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Coarse-to-Fine Annealing Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The coarse-to-fine annealing schedule is the proposed fix that masks high positional-encoding frequencies early and progressively re-enables them during training.&lt;SEP&gt;Coarse-to-Fine Annealing Schedule is a regularization strategy applied to positional-encoding frequencies to stabilize deformation learning by introducing motion detail progressively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Local Minima">
  <data key="d0">Local Minima</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Local minima are undesirable optimization outcomes into which bundle adjustment can fall when the pose-gradient landscape becomes spiky.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Frequency NeRF">
  <data key="d0">Low-Frequency NeRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Low-frequency NeRF is the early-training regime that provides smooth pose gradients and helps the optimizer find correct camera registration globally.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deformation Fields">
  <data key="d0">Deformation Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Deformation fields are the target of the concurrent coarse-to-fine frequency trick used in Nerfies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Extrinsic Pose">
  <data key="d0">Extrinsic Pose</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Extrinsic pose is the camera pose parameter domain to which BARF applies the coarse-to-fine positional-encoding strategy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Synthetic Blender Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Synthetic Blender Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Synthetic Blender scenes are experimental datasets used to evaluate BARF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real Forward-Facing Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Real Forward-Facing Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Real forward-facing scenes are experimental datasets used to evaluate BARF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pose-Free NeRF Training">
  <data key="d0">Pose-Free NeRF Training</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pose-free NeRF training is the capability enabled by BARF through recovery of camera poses and reconstructions without accurate initial cameras.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dense Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Dense Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Dense reconstruction is a field to which the paper connects the radiance-field literature.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pose-Refining NeRF Systems">
  <data key="d0">Pose-Refining NeRF Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Pose-refining NeRF systems are subsequent systems for which BARF serves as a regular reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian-Splatting Systems">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian-Splatting Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian-splatting systems are subsequent systems for which BARF serves as a regular reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-252e33536ee596bbdc69a5c1521289c2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2104-06405/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875732</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mip-NeRF 360: Unbounded Anti-Aliased Neural Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">Mip-NeRF 360: Unbounded Anti-Aliased Neural Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Mip-NeRF 360: Unbounded Anti-Aliased Neural Radiance Fields is a paper published on 2021-11-23 that extends Mip-NeRF to unbounded 360-degree scenes and introduces new parameterization, distillation, and regularization techniques for neural radiance fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dor Verbin">
  <data key="d0">Dor Verbin</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dor Verbin is an author of Mip-NeRF 360: Unbounded Anti-Aliased Neural Radiance Fields.&lt;SEP&gt;Dor Verbin is an author of MERF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c8a391c236226d67322607a99b2e56</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2302-12249/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876128</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Unbounded 360-Degree Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Unbounded 360-Degree Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Unbounded 360-degree scenes are outdoor environments and large indoor spaces with arbitrary scene depth and camera rotation around a point.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Non-Linear Scene Parameterization">
  <data key="d0">Non-Linear Scene Parameterization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-linear scene parameterization is a method that contracts unbounded 3D coordinates into a bounded domain while preserving near-field linearity and smoothly compressing far-field content.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Online Distillation Scheme">
  <data key="d0">Online Distillation Scheme</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Online distillation scheme is a method in which a small proposal MLP predicts where mass lies along a ray under supervision from a larger radiance MLP to improve hierarchical sampling efficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distortion-Based Regularizer">
  <data key="d0">Distortion-Based Regularizer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Distortion-based regularizer is a method that penalizes radiance contributions smeared along a ray to suppress floaters and background haze in large-scene neural radiance fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Proposal MLP">
  <data key="d0">Proposal MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Proposal MLP is a small neural network used to predict where mass lies along a ray in the online distillation scheme.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NDC Trick">
  <data key="d0">NDC Trick</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NDC trick is a classical technique that the paper extends to non-forward-facing captures through its non-linear contraction approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mip-NeRF360 Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Mip-NeRF360 Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Mip-NeRF360 Dataset is the new 360-degree benchmark introduced with the paper and later becomes a standard evaluation suite for unbounded radiance-field methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mean-Squared Error">
  <data key="d0">Mean-Squared Error</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Mean-squared error is the evaluation quantity that is reduced by 57% relative to Mip-NeRF according to the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Depth Maps">
  <data key="d0">Depth Maps</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Depth maps are outputs that the paper reports as clean for highly intricate real-world captures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Shape-Radiance Ambiguities">
  <data key="d0">Shape-Radiance Ambiguities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Shape-radiance ambiguities are artifacts in unbounded captures that contribute to visually disturbing rendering errors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Background Haze">
  <data key="d0">Background Haze</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Background haze is an artifact affecting large-scene neural radiance fields that the distortion-based regularizer suppresses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zip-NeRF">
  <data key="d0">Zip-NeRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Zip-NeRF is a subsequent system in the corpus that targets the same unbounded radiance-field regime and uses the Mip-NeRF360 dataset.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d0dff9058b6eb6ab9730d5170f51b92d</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2111-12077/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Instant3D: Fast Text-to-3D with Sparse-View Generation and Large Reconstruction Model">
  <data key="d0">Instant3D: Fast Text-to-3D with Sparse-View Generation and Large Reconstruction Model</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Instant3D: Fast Text-to-3D with Sparse-View Generation and Large Reconstruction Model is a paper dated 2023-11-10 that presents a fast feed-forward Text-to-3D approach based on sparse-view generation and a large reconstruction model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jiahao Li">
  <data key="d0">Jiahao Li</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jiahao Li is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zexiang Xu">
  <data key="d0">Zexiang Xu</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Zexiang Xu is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fujun Luan">
  <data key="d0">Fujun Luan</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Fujun Luan is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Yinghao Xu">
  <data key="d0">Yinghao Xu</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Yinghao Xu is an author of the Instant3D paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22bc14784620637c470939b2097cd200</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-06214/paper.md</data>
