  <data key="d0">Arash Vahdat</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Arash Vahdat is an author of the AGG paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The neural network in AGG is trained to map directly from an image to the parameters of a Gaussian set.&lt;SEP&gt;The Neural Network is an underlying model component that can be edited and trained on a new task by using the Tiny-CUDA-NN PyTorch Extension.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian Locations">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Locations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian locations are the predicted positions of Gaussian primitives that AGG separates from appearance attribute prediction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Appearance Attributes">
  <data key="d0">Appearance Attributes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Appearance attributes are the non-location properties predicted by AGG, including opacity, colour via spherical harmonics, scale, and rotation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hybrid Intermediate Representation">
  <data key="d0">Hybrid Intermediate Representation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The hybrid intermediate representation is the mechanism through which AGG's two prediction streams interact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Gaussian Super-Resolution Module">
  <data key="d0">3D Gaussian Super-Resolution Module</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The 3D Gaussian super-resolution module is the downstream stage that upsamples primitive count and refines local detail.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Feed-Forward Gaussian Predictors">
  <data key="d0">Feed-Forward Gaussian Predictors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Feed-forward Gaussian predictors are a broader family of learned models that directly predict Gaussian-based 3D content without per-instance optimization loops.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Learned Amortized Inference">
  <data key="d0">Learned Amortized Inference</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Learned amortized inference is the approach toward which AGG and related models shift 3D content creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Content Creation">
  <data key="d0">3D Content Creation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">3D content creation is the application area in which AGG and related Gaussian predictors operate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d81fdba1f24c6b674084889fda5183d4</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2401-04099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2D Image Inputs">
  <data key="d0">2D Image Inputs</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">2D Image Inputs are the input data used by NeuS to reconstruct objects and scenes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/totoro97-neus/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cameras_xxx.npz">
  <data key="d0">Cameras_xxx.npz</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cameras_xxx.npz is a camera-parameter data file used in the repository data convention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/totoro97-neus/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="World_mat_xx">
  <data key="d0">World_mat_xx</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">World_mat_xx is a matrix entry in the camera data format that denotes the world-to-image projection matrix.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/totoro97-neus/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scale_mat_xx">
  <data key="d0">Scale_mat_xx</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Scale_mat_xx is a matrix entry in the camera data format that denotes the normalization matrix.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/totoro97-neus/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Exp_runner.py">
  <data key="d0">Exp_runner.py</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Exp_runner.py is the script used to train NeuS, validate meshes, and run view interpolation commands.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/totoro97-neus/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875926</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="View Interpolation">
  <data key="d0">View Interpolation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">View Interpolation is a repository operation that renders interpolated views between image indices from a trained model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e0eea83c50adbc2bba8e169fafb1efca</data>
