</node>
<node id="DNeRF">
  <data key="d0">DNeRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DNeRF is a training category or method associated with synthetic scenes stored under `data/dnerf`.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bouncingballs">
  <data key="d0">Bouncingballs</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">bouncingballs is a synthetic scene used as an example for DNeRF training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DyNeRF">
  <data key="d0">DyNeRF</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">DyNeRF is a training category or method associated with scenes that require frame extraction, point-cloud generation, and point-cloud downsampling before training.&lt;SEP&gt;DyNeRF is a follow-up method cited as part of the wave of work seeded by the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61a153082bbdd12d0fece3ecc8442ad9</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2105-06468/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cut_Roasted_Beef">
  <data key="d0">Cut_Roasted_Beef</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">cut_roasted_beef is a DyNeRF scene used as an example workflow for preprocessing and training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="preprocess_dynerf.py">
  <data key="d0">preprocess_dynerf.py</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">preprocess_dynerf.py is a script used to extract frames from each video for a DyNeRF scene.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="colmap.sh">
  <data key="d0">colmap.sh</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">colmap.sh is a script used to compute or generate point clouds from input data with COLMAP.&lt;SEP&gt;`colmap.sh` is a helper shell script that generates point clouds from input data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d8dc07a758da2f544255725b8c6e1a2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/hustvl-4dgaussians/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778875929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="downsample_point.py">
  <data key="d0">downsample_point.py</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">downsample_point.py is a script used to downsample generated point clouds.&lt;SEP&gt;`downsample_point.py` is a script that downsamples generated point clouds by structure-from-motion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e94987ca7ac98962142f83ef53476d0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d8dc07a758da2f544255725b8c6e1a2</data>
