</node>
<node id="Single-View-to-3D Problem">
  <data key="d0">Single-View-to-3D Problem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The single-view-to-3D problem is the under-constrained task of inferring 3D structure from one image, where infinitely many 3D shapes can project to the same image.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876006</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ravi Ramamoorthi">
  <data key="d0">Ravi Ramamoorthi</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Ravi Ramamoorthi is an author of NeRF: Representing Scenes as Neural Radiance Fields for View Synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;Ravi Ramamoorthi is a listed author of the NeRF paper.&lt;SEP&gt;Ravi Ramamoorthi is an author of the cited NeRF paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45d73dd21f95946d74e1b943beb1d384&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee99e1fe0369d50218c77432ff216939</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/bmild-nerf/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876879</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Viewpoint-Conditional Diffusion Model">
  <data key="d0">Viewpoint-Conditional Diffusion Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The viewpoint-conditional diffusion model is a fine-tuned Stable-Diffusion-style 2D diffusion model that denoises a target object image conditioned on an input image and a relative camera transformation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stable-Diffusion-Style 2D Diffusion Model">
  <data key="d0">Stable-Diffusion-Style 2D Diffusion Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Stable-Diffusion-style 2D diffusion model is the backbone that Zero-1-to-3 fine-tunes to model viewpoint-conditioned image generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Relative Camera Transformation">
  <data key="d0">Relative Camera Transformation</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The relative camera transformation is the conditioning signal expressed as elevation, azimuth, and radius for generating target object views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Objaverse Synthetic 3D Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Objaverse Synthetic 3D Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Objaverse synthetic 3D dataset provides rendered training data at randomized viewpoints for training the Zero-1-to-3 model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Latent Diffusion Objective">
  <data key="d0">Latent Diffusion Objective</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The latent diffusion objective is the training objective used to fit triplets of source view, relative pose, and target view.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coordinate-Based MLP">
  <data key="d0">Coordinate-Based MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Coordinate-Based MLP is the fully-connected network used to encode the continuous volumetric function in Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="5D Input">
  <data key="d0">5D Input</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">5D Input consists of a 3D spatial location and a 2D viewing direction that are provided to the network in Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Volume Density">
  <data key="d0">Volume Density</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Volume Density is one of the outputs predicted by the network in Neural Radiance Fields for queried 5D coordinates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="View-Dependent Emitted Radiance">
  <data key="d0">View-Dependent Emitted Radiance</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">View-Dependent Emitted Radiance is one of the outputs predicted by the network in Neural Radiance Fields for queried 5D coordinates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sinusoidal Positional Encoding">
  <data key="d0">Sinusoidal Positional Encoding</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Sinusoidal Positional Encoding is applied to input coordinates before the MLP to lift them into a higher-frequency space that helps fit high-frequency scene content.&lt;SEP&gt;Sinusoidal Positional Encoding is a method credited with enabling coordinate MLPs to fit high frequencies in the original NeRF framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1234ddae6b39821bcc34ebe785c813</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-10/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876754</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hierarchical Coarse-To-Fine Sampling">
  <data key="d0">Hierarchical Coarse-To-Fine Sampling</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Hierarchical Coarse-To-Fine Sampling is a design choice in which a coarse network estimates mass along each ray and a fine network importance-samples around those locations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Single-Image-to-3D Line">
  <data key="d0">Single-Image-to-3D Line</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The single-image-to-3D line is the research direction focused on generating 3D structure from a single image.</data>
