  <data key="d5">1778876879</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implicit Coordinate-Based Differentiable Optimized Per-Scene Paradigm">
  <data key="d0">Implicit Coordinate-Based Differentiable Optimized Per-Scene Paradigm</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Implicit Coordinate-Based Differentiable Optimized Per-Scene Paradigm is the paradigm established by Neural Radiance Fields and described as dominating 3D reconstruction since the paper's result.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876010</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Surface-Reconstruction Line">
  <data key="d0">Surface-Reconstruction Line</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Surface-Reconstruction Line is the line of follow-up work that includes UNISURF, NeuS, and VolSDF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876010</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="github.com/bmild/nerf">
  <data key="d0">github.com/bmild/nerf</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">github.com/bmild/nerf is the reference implementation of NeRF and is described as the canonical starting point.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876010</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Differentiable Rasterisation">
  <data key="d0">Differentiable Rasterisation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Differentiable Rasterisation is the rendering approach used to project and render the 3D Gaussians in the proposed pipeline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876014</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Structure From Motion">
  <data key="d0">Structure From Motion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Structure From Motion is a standard pass used to produce the sparse point cloud that seeds the optimisation.&lt;SEP&gt;Structure From Motion is an offline stage that vanilla 3DGS requires for accurate per-image camera poses.&lt;SEP&gt;Structure From Motion is a method listed in the paper metadata as one of the methods associated with the work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a20b3ebc3dcc9adfa50adfa770ad6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7411808cb359d1b718d660e9dbd2a39e</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-06741/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2108-10869/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="INRIA">
  <data key="d0">INRIA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">INRIA is the organization associated with the open reference implementation mentioned in the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md</data>
