</node>
<node id="Basis Convention">
  <data key="d0">Basis Convention</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Basis Convention refers to the spherical-harmonic basis choice used by the gsplat library and documented in the supplement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876134</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Python API">
  <data key="d0">Python API</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Python API is the accompanying interface in gsplat that exposes components of the forward and backward passes individually.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876134</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Forward Pass">
  <data key="d0">Forward Pass</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Forward Pass is a computational component of gsplat that is documented in the supplement and exposed individually through the Python API.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876134</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Backward Pass">
  <data key="d0">Backward Pass</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Backward Pass is a computational component of gsplat that is documented in the supplement and exposed individually through the Python API.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876134</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rasteriser Interface">
  <data key="d0">Rasteriser Interface</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Rasteriser Interface is the gsplat interface that research extensions and SLAM systems have reused or imitated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876135</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GaussianSplatting Ecosystem">
  <data key="d0">GaussianSplatting Ecosystem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">GaussianSplatting Ecosystem is the broader ecosystem for which the supplement functions as the canonical low-level reference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876135</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kerbl et al.">
  <data key="d0">Kerbl et al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Kerbl et al. are the authors of the original 3DGS paper referenced as prior work that introduced the representation and high-level rendering pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Kerbl et al. are the authors associated with the original 3D Gaussian Splatting paper that introduced Adaptive Density Control.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add2de44399af98e378bc92e1b3f3d85</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2404-06109/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876239</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Nerfies: Deformable Neural Radiance Fields is a paper published on 2020-11-25 that presents Nerfies for deformable scene reconstruction and view synthesis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic and 4D Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic and 4D Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic and 4D Reconstruction is the sub-topic under which the paper is categorized.&lt;SEP&gt;Dynamic and 4D Reconstruction is the sub-topic under which 4D Gaussian Splatting For Real-Time Dynamic Scene Rendering is categorized.&lt;SEP&gt;Dynamic and 4D Reconstruction is a subtopic concerned with reconstructing changing scenes over time, including selfie videos modeled as 4D scenes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb7662ca60286f5c929b6bb92d667dfd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb1234ddae6b39821bcc34ebe785c813</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2310-08528/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-10/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876754</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Continuous Volumetric Deformation Field">
  <data key="d0">Continuous Volumetric Deformation Field</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Continuous Volumetric Deformation Field is the key extension in Nerfies that maps each observed 5D coordinate into a canonical template space.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Canonical Template Space">
  <data key="d0">Canonical Template Space</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Canonical Template Space is the shared reference space into which observed coordinates are mapped before fitting a standard NeRF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Positional-Encoding Frequencies">
  <data key="d0">Positional-Encoding Frequencies</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Positional-Encoding Frequencies are the frequency components of the deformation network encoding that are annealed during optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Elastic Energy Regularizer">
  <data key="d0">Elastic Energy Regularizer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Elastic Energy Regularizer is a regularization method borrowed from physical-simulation literature that penalizes non-rigid Jacobian distortion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jacobian">
  <data key="d0">Jacobian</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacobian is the deformation quantity whose non-rigid distortion is penalized by the elastic energy regularizer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Two-Phone Rig">
  <data key="d0">Two-Phone Rig</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Two-Phone Rig is the capture setup used to record training video and time-synchronized validation frames from different viewpoints.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Video">
  <data key="d0">Training Video</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Video is the video recorded by one phone in the two-phone rig for model training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Validation Frames">
  <data key="d0">Validation Frames</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Validation Frames are time-synchronized frames recorded by a second phone from a different viewpoint for evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876146</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Canonical-Template-Plus-Deformation-Field Formulation">
  <data key="d0">Canonical-Template-Plus-Deformation-Field Formulation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Canonical-Template-Plus-Deformation-Field Formulation is the formulation established by Nerfies that combines a canonical template with a learned deformation field.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Topologically Varying Scenes">
  <data key="d0">Topologically Varying Scenes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Topologically Varying Scenes are scenes with topology changes that HyperNeRF later addresses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic-NeRF Literature">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic-NeRF Literature</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic-NeRF Literature is the body of work in which the elastic regularizer and coarse-to-fine encoding schedule recur.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Casually Captured Deformable Capture">
  <data key="d0">Casually Captured Deformable Capture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Casually Captured Deformable Capture is the framing introduced by Nerfies for monocular capture of deforming subjects in casual settings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Dynamic View Synthesis">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Dynamic View Synthesis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular Dynamic View Synthesis is a strand of work seeded by the casually captured deformable capture framing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Handheld Phone">
  <data key="d0">Handheld Phone</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Handheld Phone is the casual capture device used to record non-rigidly deforming subjects for Nerfies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Physical-Simulation Literature">
  <data key="d0">Physical-Simulation Literature</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Physical-Simulation Literature is the source domain from which the elastic energy regularizer is borrowed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-640801c18546ebea4632cd80bbad0951</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2011-12948/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876147</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF MLP">
  <data key="d0">NeRF MLP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF MLP is the neural-network component that Plenoxels replaces.&lt;SEP&gt;NeRF MLP is the neural component queried across many sampled points per ray in earlier implicit methods such as DreamFusion and Magic123.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d7bbefe39a52948bd9d7195856ac2b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2309-16653/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876451</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sparse Voxel Grid">
  <data key="d0">Sparse Voxel Grid</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sparse Voxel Grid is the representation used by Plenoxels and contains spherical-harmonics coefficients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Spherical-Harmonics Coefficients">
  <data key="d0">Spherical-Harmonics Coefficients</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Spherical-Harmonics Coefficients are the values stored in the sparse voxel grid used by Plenoxels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gradient Descent">
  <data key="d0">Gradient Descent</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Gradient Descent is the optimization method used to directly optimize the spherical-harmonics coefficients in Plenoxels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876204</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CUDA Kernels">
  <data key="d0">CUDA Kernels</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CUDA Kernels are provided by the repository to support core operations used in the implementation.&lt;SEP&gt;CUDA kernels are the low-level computational components in Gsplat that downstream methods integrate with.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876468</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Total Variation Regularization">
  <data key="d0">Total Variation Regularization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Total Variation Regularization is one of the operations supported by the CUDA kernels in the repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Unbounded-Scene Voxel Layout">
  <data key="d0">Unbounded-Scene Voxel Layout</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Unbounded-Scene Voxel Layout is one of the voxel-layout operations supported by the CUDA kernels in the repository.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eaaf691c43304c4a589967639d84b94f</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/sxyu-svox2/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876205</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
