<node id="Gsplat">
  <data key="d0">Gsplat</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Gsplat is an open-source library for CUDA-accelerated rasterization of gaussians with Python bindings, designed to be faster, more memory efficient, and feature rich.&lt;SEP&gt;Gsplat is an open-source library for Gaussian splatting and is the software project described in the repository.&lt;SEP&gt;Gsplat is an open, permissive CUDA library for Gaussian splatting that re-implements the core differentiable rasterization of 3D Gaussians with explicit, documented gradients suitable for research extensions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfb5c9e689ffa78ae20907ec96c23e19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50e33da257497d62c9963654a61913d2</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/about.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876467</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Rendering of Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d0">3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Rendering of Radiance Fields</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Rendering of Radiance Fields is the SIGGRAPH paper that inspired gsplat.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PPISP">
  <data key="d0">PPISP</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">PPISP is an integrated method in gsplat that serves as an alternative to bilateral grid for compensating training views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bilateral Grid">
  <data key="d0">Bilateral Grid</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Bilateral Grid is a method referenced as the alternative baseline to PPISP for compensating training views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f175249759ca8a973f8918ff16dfac34</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nerfstudio-project-gsplat/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
