<node id="Background Color Randomization">
  <data key="d0">Background Color Randomization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Background Color Randomization is a training method used during NeRF training to prevent the model from learning a fixed solid background instead of transparency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF Training">
  <data key="d0">NeRF Training</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF Training is the training process discussed in relation to randomized background colors and masking away training pixels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transparency">
  <data key="d0">Transparency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Transparency is described as a property indicated by training data and as a desired property in the learned model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zero Density">
  <data key="d0">Zero Density</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Zero Density is the model behavior that background color randomization is intended to teach so that transparency can be represented correctly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Image `xyz.*`">
  <data key="d0">Training Image `xyz.*`</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Training Image `xyz.*` is any training image that may contain dynamic objects and can be paired with a mask file.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="`dynamic_mask_xyz.png`">
  <data key="d0">`dynamic_mask_xyz.png`</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">`dynamic_mask_xyz.png` is a required PNG mask file placed beside a training image to mark masked-away regions for NeRF training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Masked-Away Regions">
  <data key="d0">Masked-Away Regions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Masked-Away Regions are image regions indicated by non-zero pixel values in the dynamic mask and excluded from NeRF training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-67aca36ec8eb49d9f01fa3055f69d8fd</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
