  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Python Bindings">
  <data key="d0">Python Bindings</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Python bindings are provided for Instant-NGP so that its features can be used for controlled and automated experiments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TCNN_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES">
  <data key="d0">TCNN_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">TCNN_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES is an environment variable that can be set when automatic GPU architecture detection fails.&lt;SEP&gt;TCNN_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES is an environment variable used to select or optimize compilation for a specific GPU architecture when automatic GPU architecture detection fails.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b9702cfd82aaa0f9d50ba7409bbecf8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GPU Architecture Detection">
  <data key="d0">GPU Architecture Detection</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">GPU Architecture Detection is the automatic detection process that may fail when multiple GPUs are installed.&lt;SEP&gt;GPU architecture detection is an automatic process that may fail, especially when multiple GPUs are installed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b9702cfd82aaa0f9d50ba7409bbecf8</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Common GPUs">
  <data key="d0">Common GPUs</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Common GPUs are listed in a table with architecture values including H100, 40X0, 30X0, A100, 20X0, TITAN V or V100, 10X0 or TITAN Xp, 9X0, and K80.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876504</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PyTorch Extension">
  <data key="d0">PyTorch Extension</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The PyTorch extension is a Tiny-CUDA-NN extension suggested for building new models from hash encoding and fast neural networks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0096ef684fc11385dab039c4985ae213</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/nvlabs-instant-ngp/readme.md</data>
