  <data key="d2">Xuelong Li is an author of GS-SLAM: Dense Visual SLAM with 3D Gaussian Splatting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dense RGB-D SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Dense RGB-D SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dense RGB-D SLAM is the problem setting addressed by GS-SLAM through incremental scene-scale capture and camera tracking with RGB-D input.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Neural Implicit Surface Rendering">
  <data key="d0">Neural Implicit Surface Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Neural Implicit Surface Rendering is a geometry reconstruction approach used by earlier neural SLAM methods and is coupled with ray sampling and MLP queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coarse-to-Fine Selection of Reliable Gaussians">
  <data key="d0">Coarse-to-Fine Selection of Reliable Gaussians</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Coarse-to-Fine Selection of Reliable Gaussians is a GS-SLAM strategy that focuses pose optimisation on confidently observed regions and reduces the effect of noisy or recently spawned primitives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Adaptive Expansion Strategy">
  <data key="d0">Adaptive Expansion Strategy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Adaptive Expansion Strategy is the GS-SLAM mapping strategy that adds new Gaussians where the map fails to explain pixels and prunes Gaussians that drift from the surface.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Differentiable Splatting Rasteriser">
  <data key="d0">Differentiable Splatting Rasteriser</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Differentiable Splatting Rasteriser is the rendering mechanism used by GS-SLAM together with Gaussians to obtain efficient scene updates and visualisation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-Time Rendering SLAM Methods">
  <data key="d0">Real-Time Rendering SLAM Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-Time Rendering SLAM Methods is the method category within which GS-SLAM achieves state-of-the-art rendering quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monocular Setting">
  <data key="d0">Monocular Setting</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Monocular Setting is the more difficult problem setting addressed by Gaussian Splatting SLAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Explicit Gaussian Primitives">
  <data key="d0">Explicit Gaussian Primitives</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Explicit Gaussian Primitives are presented as a serious option for live dense SLAM and as a basis for later Gaussian-based incremental reconstruction work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Live Dense SLAM">
  <data key="d0">Live Dense SLAM</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Live Dense SLAM is the application area in which explicit Gaussian primitives were established as a serious option.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian-Based Incremental Reconstruction">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian-Based Incremental Reconstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian-Based Incremental Reconstruction is the follow-on literature seeded by GS-SLAM and Gaussian Splatting SLAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ef4e01183cb872fcf6e3325fde57a921</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-11700/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876848</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LargeReconstructionModel (LRM)">
  <data key="d0">LargeReconstructionModel (LRM)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LargeReconstructionModel (LRM) is the earlier reconstruction model whose TransformerArchitecture template TripoSR preserves and tightens while outperforming its roughly five-second inference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cross-Attention Transformer">
  <data key="d0">Cross-Attention Transformer</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cross-Attention Transformer is the transformer component in the LargeReconstructionModel template that predicts a triplane-parameterised volumetric representation from encoded image features.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Triplane-Parameterised Volumetric Representation">
  <data key="d0">Triplane-Parameterised Volumetric Representation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Triplane-Parameterised Volumetric Representation is the internal 3D representation predicted by the architecture described in the report.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quality-Aware Filtering">
  <data key="d0">Quality-Aware Filtering</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Quality-Aware Filtering is the data cleaning approach used to de-emphasise low-quality multi-view supervision in TripoSR training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kernel Scheduling">
  <data key="d0">Kernel Scheduling</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Kernel Scheduling is an inference engineering method used to accelerate TripoSR.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mixed-Precision Execution">
  <data key="d0">Mixed-Precision Execution</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Mixed-Precision Execution is an inference engineering method used to accelerate TripoSR.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2403.02151">
  <data key="d0">2403.02151</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">2403.02151 is the arXiv identifier listed for TripoSR: Fast 3D Object Reconstruction from a Single Image.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multi-View Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">Multi-View Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-View Diffusion is a downstream method paired with TripoSR in single-image-to-3D pipelines in the style of Instant3D.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-da7ad32a7899b18880ae81f4444362ce</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-02151/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
