<node id="Feature Field Distillation">
  <data key="d0">Feature Field Distillation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Feature Field Distillation is the process of distilling arbitrary-channel semantic features into a 3D representation for viewpoint-consistent rendering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876923</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NeRF-Based Feature Distillation">
  <data key="d0">NeRF-Based Feature Distillation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NeRF-based feature distillation is an earlier approach that lifts 2D foundation model features into a 3D radiance field but suffers from slow rendering and continuity artefacts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876923</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CLIP-LSeg">
  <data key="d0">CLIP-LSeg</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CLIP-LSeg is a 2D foundation model whose features can be distilled to produce a language-queryable 3D scene for open-vocabulary editing and semantic segmentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876923</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SAM">
  <data key="d0">SAM</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">SAM is a 2D foundation model whose features can be distilled into a Gaussian field to enable point- and box-prompted 3D-consistent segmentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Semantic Segmentation">
  <data key="d0">Semantic Segmentation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Semantic segmentation is an application enabled by distilled SAM and CLIP-LSeg features in Feature 3DGS.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Point Prompting">
  <data key="d0">Point Prompting</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Point prompting is a render-time interaction mode supported through the 2D SAM API for 3D-consistent segmentation and radiance field manipulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bounding-Box Prompting">
  <data key="d0">Bounding-Box Prompting</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Bounding-box prompting is a render-time interaction mode supported through the 2D SAM API for 3D-consistent segmentation and radiance field manipulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-44c8d46282ec234e9b7dfd7ddc08a05b</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-03203/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778876925</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
