<node id="LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation">
  <data key="d0">LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation is a paper published on February 7, 2024, that presents LGM for high-resolution 3D content generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zhaoxi Chen">
  <data key="d0">Zhaoxi Chen</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Zhaoxi Chen is an author of the paper LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Xiaokang Chen">
  <data key="d0">Xiaokang Chen</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Xiaokang Chen is an author of the paper LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tengfei Wang">
  <data key="d0">Tengfei Wang</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Tengfei Wang is an author of the paper LGM: Large Multi-View Gaussian Model for High-Resolution 3D Content Creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Asymmetric U-Net">
  <data key="d0">Asymmetric U-Net</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Asymmetric U-Net is the network in the LGM pipeline that operates on the multi-view image stack and predicts per-pixel Gaussian features.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Differentiable Rendering">
  <data key="d0">Differentiable Rendering</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Differentiable Rendering is the fusion mechanism used in LGM to combine Gaussian features across views into the final 3D Gaussian field.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3D Gaussian Field">
  <data key="d0">3D Gaussian Field</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">3D Gaussian Field is the final 3D representation formed in LGM by fusing per-pixel Gaussian features across multiple views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gaussian Representations">
  <data key="d0">Gaussian Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gaussian Representations are explicit 3D representations that the paper identifies as part of a broader shift in amortised 3D generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877008</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implicit Field">
  <data key="d0">Implicit Field</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Implicit Field is a volumetric style of 3D representation whose high-resolution prediction is described as memory-heavy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Text Prompt">
  <data key="d0">Text Prompt</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Text Prompt is one of the input modalities from which LGM can generate high-resolution 3D content.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="3DTopia/LGM">
  <data key="d0">3DTopia/LGM</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">3DTopia/LGM is the open-source repository associated with the paper.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="512-Pixel Training Resolution">
  <data key="d0">512-Pixel Training Resolution</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">512-Pixel Training Resolution is the training resolution at which LGM generates 3D content in the described end-to-end system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
  <data key="d4">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2402-05054/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1778877009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Five Seconds of Inference">
  <data key="d0">Five Seconds of Inference</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Five Seconds of Inference is the approximate inference time within which LGM generates 3D content at 512-pixel training resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd7bc6ade0fccf24f57100e1dd5adb7</data>
