<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="Neural Radiance Fields">
  <data key="d7">3.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees accelerates Neural Radiance Fields inference by more than three orders of magnitude.&lt;SEP&gt;PlenOctrees is identified as a follow-up spawned by Neural Radiance Fields.&lt;SEP&gt;PlenOctrees converts a trained Neural Radiance Fields model into a sparse octree representation for real-time rendering.</data>
  <data key="d9">acceleration,follow-up,model conversion,real-time rendering,rendering,research lineage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec770f62777c513047108cb79ba7aa75</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-15/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876606</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="MLP">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees relies on densely evaluating a trained NeRF's MLP on a 3D grid and then discarding the MLP for render-time use.</data>
  <data key="d9">baking,model transformation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="Spherical-Harmonic Expansion">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees uses spherical-harmonic coefficients to preserve view-dependent effects such as specularities without a viewing-direction input to the MLP.</data>
  <data key="d9">appearance modeling,specularity preservation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="PlenOctree">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees stores pruned, pre-tabulated MLP outputs in the sparse octree artifact called the PlenOctree.</data>
  <data key="d9">representation,storage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="150 FPS">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees renders 800x800 frames at over 150 FPS.</data>
  <data key="d9">performance,real-time rendering</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="Plenoxels">
  <data key="d7">3.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees is identified as the immediate predecessor of Plenoxels.&lt;SEP&gt;PlenOctrees is described as the immediate methodological predecessor of Plenoxels.&lt;SEP&gt;Plenoxels pushed further the inference-speed tradeoff pattern introduced by PlenOctrees.</data>
  <data key="d9">method lineage,method progression,predecessor,speed optimization</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0561cfd70b96f995d3cdeb043981668&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec770f62777c513047108cb79ba7aa75</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2112-05131/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-15/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876607</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="MERF">
  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The factorization used by PlenOctrees recurs in subsequent baking pipelines such as MERF.&lt;SEP&gt;MERF is positioned against PlenOctrees by addressing unbounded large-scale scenes that PlenOctrees does not scale to.</data>
  <data key="d9">comparison,factorization,method influence,scalability gap</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c8a391c236226d67322607a99b2e56</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2302-12249/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876151</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="SNeRG">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The factorization used by PlenOctrees recurs in subsequent baking pipelines such as SNeRG.</data>
  <data key="d9">factorization,method influence</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="Occupancy Octree Plus SH Appearance">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees is described as using the factorization of an occupancy octree plus spherical-harmonic appearance.</data>
  <data key="d9">factorization,representation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-efee674c2ffd20246abfb52e90ffa964</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2103-14024/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874494</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="PlenOctrees" target="Real-Time Rendering">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">PlenOctrees is presented as a method for real-time rendering of Neural Radiance Fields.</data>
  <data key="d9">acceleration,application</data>
