<edge source="3D Gaussian Splatting" target="Scaffold-GS">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Scaffold-GS is presented as a structured replacement for vanilla 3D Gaussian Splatting that addresses redundant primitives and poor geometry sharing.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is positioned within the Gaussian splatting family by replacing free Gaussians with anchor points that emit view-conditioned offsets.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is presented as follow-on work that restructures the free Gaussian representation introduced by 3D Gaussian Splatting.&lt;SEP&gt;Scaffold-GS is described as a structural variant related to Gaussian Splatting that changes the primitive itself rather than the densification schedule.</data>
