<edge source="3D Gaussian Splatting" target="SuGaR">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">SuGaR is described as the surface story for splatting, extending the Gaussian splatting line toward manifold regularisation and mesh extraction.&lt;SEP&gt;SuGaR is described as follow-on work triggered by the paper and builds on Gaussian-based representations for surface alignment and mesh extraction.&lt;SEP&gt;SuGaR is described as a surface-aware variant within the 3D Gaussian Splatting family.&lt;SEP&gt;SuGaR is described as a structural variant related to Gaussian Splatting that changes the primitive itself rather than the densification schedule.&lt;SEP&gt;SuGaR addresses a practical gap in 3D Gaussian Splatting by enabling structured mesh extraction from its unstructured Gaussian primitive cloud.</data>
  <data key="d9">extension,follow-on work,geometry extraction,method extension,primitive design,splatting,structural variant,surface reconstruction,surface-aware method,variant</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-1a8a7270af8c939590a0f9c7697a5b90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d445282e0f2225e2a32ef51280563a09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3243555eac5ed46cea7fe8cead1666bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add2de44399af98e378bc92e1b3f3d85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c76c39f593d0f7cf762ef607bb98a3db</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-25/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2308-04079/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2312-02121/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2404-06109/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2311-12775/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876773</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="3D Gaussian Splatting" target="2D Gaussian Splatting">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">2D Gaussian Splatting is contrasted with 3D Gaussian Splatting because collapsing primitives to oriented disks removes depth ambiguity while slightly reducing view-synthesis fidelity.&lt;SEP&gt;2D Gaussian Splatting is presented as follow-on work derived from the paper's Gaussian splatting approach.&lt;SEP&gt;2D Gaussian Splatting is described as a surface-aware variant related to 3D Gaussian Splatting.&lt;SEP&gt;2D Gaussian Splatting is described as a structural variant related to Gaussian Splatting that changes the primitive itself rather than the densification schedule.&lt;SEP&gt;2D Gaussian Splatting is proposed as an alternative to 3D Gaussian Splatting because 3D Gaussian Splatting is not view-consistent for accurate geometry.</data>
