<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Score Distillation Sampling">
  <data key="d7">3.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion is described as the SDS paper and serves as the defining paper for Score Distillation Sampling in the digest.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion introduces Score Distillation Sampling as its core technical contribution for turning a diffusion model's denoising direction into an optimization signal for 3D generation.&lt;SEP&gt;Score Distillation Sampling is attributed to DreamFusion in the cited 2022 work.</data>
  <data key="d9">citation,core contribution,foundational method,method,method origin,paper identity</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d4bb138a75a3adf4eebfac8bdf1be29</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2303-11328/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876028</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="2D Text-to-Image Diffusion Model">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion uses a 2D text-to-image diffusion model as a critic to guide optimization toward matching the prompt.</data>
  <data key="d9">critic prior,uses</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875139</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="ashawkey/stable-dreamfusion">
  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">ashawkey/stable-dreamfusion is a reimplementation of DreamFusion and is described as what most people actually ran.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is associated with the open-source repository ashawkey/stable-dreamfusion.</data>
  <data key="d9">implementation,reimplementation,repository,usage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875235</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Imagen">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The original DreamFusion used proprietary Imagen weights, which motivated reliance on the public reimplementation.</data>
  <data key="d9">dependency,proprietary weights</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875139</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="3D Training Data">
  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion is described as using no 3D training data, with its prior coming entirely from a 2D diffusion model.&lt;SEP&gt;DreamFusion is described as requiring no 3D training data.</data>
  <data key="d9">absence,data independence,data requirement,supervision</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c9fd8d6d633ccb294d8ac229c312a9a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-05-05/digest.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Text-to-3D">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion addresses the text-to-3D problem by generating 3D content from natural-language prompts.</data>
  <data key="d9">generation,task</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Pretrained 2D Text-to-Image Diffusion Model">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion uses a pretrained 2D text-to-image diffusion model as its only learned prior and does not modify that model.</data>
  <data key="d9">supervision,uses</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Neural Radiance Field">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion optimizes a Neural Radiance Field initialized with random weights as its 3D scene representation.</data>
  <data key="d9">optimization,representation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="Optimization Problem">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion reframes text-to-3D from a data problem into an optimization problem against an existing image prior.</data>
  <data key="d9">formulation,reframing</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-179a41f27c8e25c365ff0d8b13bddc43</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2209-14988/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875234</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="DreamFusion" target="2D Image Prior">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">DreamFusion relies on a 2D image prior to supervise 3D optimization.</data>
