</edge>
<edge source="NeuS" target="IDR">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">NeuS is designed to obtain clean, mesh-extractable geometry like IDR while avoiding the need for input masks, and the experiments report sharper and more complete reconstructions than IDR.</data>
  <data key="d9">comparison,geometry quality</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-137c1bc42e741b7a6e96b6ddc476e477</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-10689/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874757</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="NeuS" target="DVR">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">NeuS is motivated by retaining the clean, mesh-extractable geometry associated with DVR-style surface methods without requiring per-pixel foreground masks.</data>
  <data key="d9">comparison,geometry quality</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-137c1bc42e741b7a6e96b6ddc476e477</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-10689/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874757</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="NeuS" target="Opacity Formulation">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">NeuS introduces a new opacity formulation for SDF-driven volume rendering as its main technical contribution.</data>
