<edge source="NeuS" target="VolSDF">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">NeuS and VolSDF are described as jointly defining the SDF-via-volume-rendering paradigm, with VolSDF published days later.&lt;SEP&gt;NeuS and VolSDF were published days apart and both propose unbiased SDF-to-density conversions after criticizing occupancy-based bias.&lt;SEP&gt;VolSDF is mentioned as related work alongside NeuS.&lt;SEP&gt;NeuS and VolSDF are described as sharing a failure mode in which performance degrades on large, textureless, or sparsely captured scenes.&lt;SEP&gt;VolSDF and NeuS are presented as near-contemporary foundational methods that solve the same problem with different opacity constructions.</data>
  <data key="d9">concurrent work,failure mode,foundational relation,methodological similarity,paradigm formation,reconstruction,related work,same problem,shared limitation</data>
