<edge source="VolSDF" target="Occupancy Function">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF argues that occupancy introduces bias into the surface estimate.</data>
  <data key="d9">bias critique,surface estimation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-e121a6c015eb471a5abd27b987476ced</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-20/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874999</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Daily Digest - 2026-04-20">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Daily Digest - 2026-04-20 includes VolSDF among its covered papers.</data>
  <data key="d9">coverage,paper summary</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-e121a6c015eb471a5abd27b987476ced</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/daily/2026-04-20/digest.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874999</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Photometric RGB Loss">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">MonoSDF identifies photometric RGB loss alone as too weak a constraint in settings where methods such as VolSDF degrade.</data>
  <data key="d9">limitation,weak constraint</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-39dac1db0f50be2348ba37c8912fe321</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2206-00665/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778875662</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Surface-Reconstruction Line">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF is identified as part of the Surface-Reconstruction Line spawned by NeRF.</data>
  <data key="d9">inclusion,research lineage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-ed61775b026776e3df7ec95d66d9c8df</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2003-08934/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876043</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Implicit Geometric Regularization">
  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Implicit Geometric Regularization became a building block for VolSDF.&lt;SEP&gt;VolSDF builds on Implicit Geometric Regularization as part of its formulation.</data>
  <data key="d9">building block,builds on,influence,prior work</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-f6fcd8824908a999c0b58a88cfc0f735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2002-10099/paper.md&lt;SEP&gt;examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Eikonal Regularizer">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF inherits the Eikonal regularizer to keep the distance field well-behaved.</data>
  <data key="d9">inherits,regularization</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-f6fcd8824908a999c0b58a88cfc0f735</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2002-10099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876556</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Volume-Rendering Era Surface Reconstruction Lineage">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The volume-rendering era surface reconstruction lineage is described as being led by VolSDF.</data>
  <data key="d9">led by,lineage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-f6fcd8824908a999c0b58a88cfc0f735</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2002-10099/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876556</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Volume Rendering of Neural Implicit Surfaces">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Volume Rendering of Neural Implicit Surfaces introduces VolSDF as its central framework.</data>
  <data key="d9">framework,introduces</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876835</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Laplace Cumulative Distribution Function">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF constructs density by applying the Laplace cumulative distribution function to the negative signed distance function.</data>
  <data key="d9">density construction,transformation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Bandwidth Parameter">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF uses a learnable bandwidth parameter to control the sharpness of the high-density shell around the zero level set.</data>
  <data key="d9">learnable parameter,sharpness control</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Radiance MLP">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF separates appearance into a radiance MLP while keeping shape in the signed distance function representation.</data>
  <data key="d9">appearance modeling,disentanglement</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Opacity-Approximation Error Bound">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF derives an explicit opacity-approximation error bound along a ray in terms of the bandwidth.</data>
  <data key="d9">derivation,ray integration</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="NeuralWarp">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">NeuralWarp is described as inheriting the Laplace-CDF density or a close cousin from VolSDF or NeuS.</data>
  <data key="d9">downstream influence,foundational reference</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Eikonal Loss">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF uses the Eikonal loss to keep the signed distance function metric.</data>
  <data key="d9">signed distance metric,uses</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VolSDF" target="Neural Implicit Surface">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VolSDF is designed for rendering and reconstructing neural implicit surfaces.</data>
  <data key="d9">application domain,surface modeling</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-62f6aaf4d349907fedafca12c9a53bdb</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-12052/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876836</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="SDF-via-Volume-Rendering Paradigm" target="Classical MVS">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The SDF-via-volume-rendering paradigm is described as having displaced classical MVS for high-fidelity multi-view surface reconstruction.</data>
  <data key="d9">displacement,methodological shift</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-137c1bc42e741b7a6e96b6ddc476e477</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2106-10689/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874757</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Score Distillation Sampling (SDS)" target="Variational Score Distillation (VSD)">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Variational Score Distillation generalises Score Distillation Sampling, and SDS is described as the single-particle limit of VSD with a delta posterior.</data>
  <data key="d9">generalisation,theoretical connection</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Variational Score Distillation (VSD)" target="Variational Score Network">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Variational Score Distillation updates 3D parameterisations using a learned variational score network.</data>
  <data key="d9">model component,optimisation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Variational Score Distillation (VSD)" target="Diffusion Prior">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Variational Score Distillation operates alongside a pretrained text-to-image Diffusion prior in its update process.</data>
  <data key="d9">optimisation framework,prior</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Variational Score Distillation (VSD)" target="Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG)">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Variational Score Distillation is reported to behave well across a wide range of classifier-free-guidance weights, including the standard CFG setting of 7.5.</data>
  <data key="d9">robustness,sampling behavior</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Diffusion Prior" target="Zero-1-to-3: Zero-shot One Image to 3D Object">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Zero-1-to-3 uses the resulting model as a diffusion prior.</data>
  <data key="d9">model role,prior</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-c47e36db5dfb4966f1d4d610b06ac6bc</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/repos/cvlab-columbia-zero123/about.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778877002</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Slow-to-Fast Distillation Time Schedule" target="Text-to-3D Methods">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The slow-to-fast distillation time schedule is described as reusable by other text-to-3D methods.</data>
  <data key="d9">method transfer,reusability</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Density Initialisation" target="Text-to-3D Methods">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Density initialisation is described as reusable by other text-to-3D methods.</data>
  <data key="d9">method transfer,reusability</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cbe78430d0376f4d6a3d05234413a4a0</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2305-16213/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778874762</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Variational" target="latentSplat: Autoencoding Variational Gaussians for Fast Generalizable 3D Reconstruction">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The paper lists Variational as one of its methods and describes a variational treatment of 3D Gaussian representations.</data>
  <data key="d9">categorization,method</data>
