</edge>
<edge source="Gaussian Disk" target="Accurate Geometry">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">A Gaussian disk has a single normal and fixed location, making the represented geometry view-consistent.</data>
  <data key="d9">surface representation,view consistency</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876588</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Gaussian Disk" target="Depth Distortion Term">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The depth distortion term encourages the depth distribution along each ray to be sharply peaked on a single disk.</data>
  <data key="d9">depth regularisation,ray behavior</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876588</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Gaussian Disk" target="Tangent Plane">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">A Gaussian disk intrinsically represents a tangent plane in 3D space.</data>
  <data key="d9">geometry,representation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876589</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Perspective-Correct Splatting Process" target="Ray-Splat Intersection">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The perspective-correct splatting process is derived through explicit ray-splat intersection.</data>
  <data key="d9">derivation,geometry</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1778876588</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Normal Consistency Term" target="Rendered Depth Map">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The normal consistency term encourages disk normals to agree with the gradient of the rendered depth map.</data>
  <data key="d9">depth gradient,normal regularisation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-6ec02429fab7e72a6a23d2a0f735836e</data>
  <data key="d11">examples/demo-corpus/data/research/papers/arxiv-2403-17888/paper.md</data>
